1
00:00:00,090 --> 00:00:08,500
<b>Hotel Del Luna Blu-ray Disc 7</b>
Subtitle re-timing by Jharel

2
00:00:47,681 --> 00:00:49,931
{\an8}My gosh, are you that sleepy?

3
00:01:01,195 --> 00:01:03,065
{\an8}-Is it the intern?
-Yes.

4
00:01:03,155 --> 00:01:05,735
{\an8}Yu-na needs to get her homework done,

5
00:01:06,200 --> 00:01:08,830
{\an8}but she was so sleepy.
So I was trying to keep her awake.

6
00:01:14,041 --> 00:01:15,131
Hyeon-jung.

7
00:01:15,709 --> 00:01:16,839
Does Yu-na know

8
00:01:17,044 --> 00:01:20,884
that you're planning to leave
with your younger sister after she dies?

9
00:01:21,799 --> 00:01:24,299
No, she doesn't know that yet.

10
00:01:24,468 --> 00:01:27,718
I only told her that
I was waiting for her.

11
00:01:29,973 --> 00:01:30,973
I see.

12
00:01:40,526 --> 00:01:42,186
-Welcome.
-Welcome, sir.

13
00:01:46,198 --> 00:01:49,788
Do you remember
how long it's been since you died?

14
00:01:49,993 --> 00:01:51,503
I can't remember for sure.

15
00:01:52,454 --> 00:01:53,584
Maybe about two days.

16
00:01:53,956 --> 00:01:55,746
-Then--
-Sir.

17
00:01:57,543 --> 00:01:59,003
Let me escort you.

18
00:02:00,254 --> 00:02:01,424
Come this way.

19
00:02:13,142 --> 00:02:14,182
Sir.

20
00:02:14,810 --> 00:02:16,520
Are you Yun Seung-beom,

21
00:02:16,895 --> 00:02:19,355
the eldest grandson
of the Yeongju Yun family

22
00:02:19,523 --> 00:02:21,533
who used to live in Beomcheon City?

23
00:02:21,900 --> 00:02:23,570
And you're 42 years old.

24
00:02:25,112 --> 00:02:26,362
Yes, that's right.

25
00:02:27,197 --> 00:02:28,737
You're still single, aren't you?

26
00:02:29,950 --> 00:02:30,990
Yes.

27
00:02:31,952 --> 00:02:34,412
I wasn't able to get married.

28
00:02:35,747 --> 00:02:37,077
I see.

29
00:02:42,671 --> 00:02:44,301
Your family must be devastated

30
00:02:44,423 --> 00:02:46,883
since the succeeding grandson
of the family died

31
00:02:47,551 --> 00:02:51,511
without even having any children.

32
00:03:03,192 --> 00:03:04,232
Ms. Choe.

33
00:03:05,527 --> 00:03:07,357
I thought you were Ms. Jang for a second.

34
00:03:07,529 --> 00:03:08,909
Why are you all dressed up?

35
00:03:08,989 --> 00:03:12,409
Mr. Kim, I think
I'll be able to leave here soon.

36
00:03:12,492 --> 00:03:15,202
I'm on my way to relieve
my 200-year-long resentment.

37
00:03:15,621 --> 00:03:17,211
Are you saying...

38
00:03:19,249 --> 00:03:20,419
He's dead.

39
00:03:22,211 --> 00:03:25,881
The very last son of that family died
and came here as a guest.

40
00:03:25,964 --> 00:03:27,094
The family tree

41
00:03:27,925 --> 00:03:31,755
of that darn family
has finally come to an end.

42
00:03:32,179 --> 00:03:36,099
I'm on my way to his funeral
so I can witness the Yeongju Yun family

43
00:03:37,976 --> 00:03:39,516
shed tears of blood.

44
00:03:40,229 --> 00:03:41,309
Ms. Choe.

45
00:03:41,813 --> 00:03:44,023
You can't cause an incident

46
00:03:45,150 --> 00:03:46,570
like 42 years ago.

47
00:03:46,735 --> 00:03:48,645
I went there because I was furious.

48
00:03:48,737 --> 00:03:51,867
But now, I'm going there
because I'm happy.

49
00:04:03,085 --> 00:04:04,875
Sanchez is still at the restaurant.

50
00:04:06,964 --> 00:04:09,764
So all I need to do is face Sanchez

51
00:04:09,841 --> 00:04:11,891
and say that I'm sorry, right?

52
00:04:12,928 --> 00:04:16,348
I can be so much more apologetic
with a shot of alcohol.

53
00:04:17,683 --> 00:04:19,023
This is sparkling water.

54
00:04:20,644 --> 00:04:22,314
Think of it as champagne, and drink it.

55
00:04:28,902 --> 00:04:31,322
It's quite bubbly. Do you have soju?

56
00:04:31,405 --> 00:04:33,775
Mix some soju in it.
Let's see if it's any good.

57
00:04:34,199 --> 00:04:36,119
If it's good, you will drink this

58
00:04:36,785 --> 00:04:37,945
instead of champagne.

59
00:04:38,036 --> 00:04:40,866
Taking away champagne and caviar
from me is the same thing

60
00:04:40,956 --> 00:04:43,826
as taking away the hot sauce and pickles
from pizza.

61
00:04:44,918 --> 00:04:47,378
And pizza reminds me of Sanchez.
I wonder if he's doing okay.

62
00:04:48,422 --> 00:04:51,592
All right. Fine. Let's go shopping
before the department store closes.

63
00:04:51,675 --> 00:04:53,635
Why is this conversation ending
with shopping?

64
00:04:53,719 --> 00:04:56,309
I'm supposed to apologize to him.
Instead of going there empty-handed

65
00:04:56,388 --> 00:04:58,178
and saying, "I'm sorry, Sanchez,"

66
00:04:58,265 --> 00:05:00,135
buying something beautiful

67
00:05:00,225 --> 00:05:02,135
and saying, "I'm sorry, Sanchez"

68
00:05:02,227 --> 00:05:04,017
would be much better.

69
00:05:06,398 --> 00:05:08,438
You just want to go shopping.

70
00:05:09,651 --> 00:05:12,491
All you need to tell Sanchez is
that Veronica left this world

71
00:05:12,571 --> 00:05:15,871
and you saw her off
at the bridge to the afterlife.

72
00:05:15,949 --> 00:05:17,449
"The bridge to the afterlife"?

73
00:05:18,410 --> 00:05:21,620
How could I see her off at the bridge
that I haven't been to myself?

74
00:05:22,914 --> 00:05:24,884
You've never been to the bridge
over the Samdo River?

75
00:05:25,792 --> 00:05:27,792
I wouldn't be here if I had been there.

76
00:05:28,462 --> 00:05:30,632
The moment you step foot on the bridge,

77
00:05:30,714 --> 00:05:32,344
it's impossible to return from it.

78
00:05:33,133 --> 00:05:34,133
Well,

79
00:05:34,509 --> 00:05:39,559
I can tell him that his girlfriend is
crossing that bridge about now.

80
00:05:40,015 --> 00:05:41,385
She's still on the bridge?

81
00:05:41,683 --> 00:05:43,233
Is the bridge that long?

82
00:05:45,645 --> 00:05:48,565
<i>Time runs at a different speed there.</i>

83
00:05:49,066 --> 00:05:52,236
<i>It doesn't take very long
to cross the bridge to the afterlife,</i>

84
00:05:52,444 --> 00:05:54,534
<i>but it's equivalent
to 49 days in this world.</i>

85
00:05:54,905 --> 00:05:56,695
While the deceased cross the bridge,

86
00:05:56,782 --> 00:05:59,532
they forget their memories of this world
one by one.

87
00:06:00,118 --> 00:06:02,828
It's not that they are forced
to stay in the afterlife.

88
00:06:03,413 --> 00:06:07,083
They don't come back
because all of their memories are gone.

89
00:06:09,920 --> 00:06:14,090
I'm pretty sure Sanchez's girlfriend is
crossing the bridge right now,

90
00:06:14,257 --> 00:06:17,297
and her memories about him are
getting erased one by one.

91
00:06:22,682 --> 00:06:24,272
It's a bitter story

92
00:06:25,519 --> 00:06:26,809
for those left behind.

93
00:06:32,067 --> 00:06:33,147
Chan-sung.

94
00:06:34,403 --> 00:06:36,243
I can promise you one thing.

95
00:06:38,198 --> 00:06:40,488
I'm 1,300 years old.

96
00:06:41,326 --> 00:06:43,616
And when I end up crossing that bridge,

97
00:06:43,787 --> 00:06:45,867
a lot of my memories will disappear.

98
00:06:47,040 --> 00:06:49,330
But I'll keep the memories of you
to the end.

99
00:06:53,672 --> 00:06:58,052
Well, I can't promise
that I'll remember you in the afterlife.

100
00:06:59,386 --> 00:07:01,806
But until I take my last step
on the bridge,

101
00:07:03,473 --> 00:07:05,103
I'll remember you.

102
00:07:19,573 --> 00:07:20,623
Okay.

103
00:07:23,535 --> 00:07:27,575
I'm sure you can do it,
given your experience of 1,300 years.

104
00:07:28,331 --> 00:07:29,331
I'll believe in you.

105
00:07:36,423 --> 00:07:38,883
But what will you remember me by?

106
00:07:40,802 --> 00:07:44,062
You were worried many times
that I might reincarnate

107
00:07:44,139 --> 00:07:45,309
as a dog or a pig.

108
00:07:46,308 --> 00:07:49,058
You sold off all of my cars,
stopped me from buying yachts,

109
00:07:49,144 --> 00:07:50,524
and took away my credit cards.

110
00:07:51,396 --> 00:07:54,606
You suggested that I should drink
sparkling water instead of champagne.

111
00:07:56,526 --> 00:07:59,986
My gosh, I only remember
these absurd things.

112
00:08:00,071 --> 00:08:02,201
I've done a lot for you.

113
00:08:02,949 --> 00:08:05,949
And especially, I won't be able to forget
about your bragging.

114
00:08:06,036 --> 00:08:08,616
I might remember the word Harvard

115
00:08:08,705 --> 00:08:11,075
instead of your name,
Koo Chan-sung, in my last moment.

116
00:08:16,421 --> 00:08:17,551
This is mine.

117
00:08:18,256 --> 00:08:21,836
Yes, I was going to order it again
since you liked the fragrance.

118
00:08:21,927 --> 00:08:23,507
But the seller disappeared.

119
00:08:23,595 --> 00:08:25,215
I brought it, so I can look into it.

120
00:08:25,639 --> 00:08:29,269
All right. I thought you stole it
from the hotel.

121
00:08:29,976 --> 00:08:31,096
That might be the case.

122
00:08:31,937 --> 00:08:34,687
Just in case, look around to see
if any of this stuff is yours.

123
00:08:35,482 --> 00:08:37,942
Did you really steal from my hotel?

124
00:08:41,905 --> 00:08:44,065
Look thoroughly
if you see your stuff here.

125
00:08:55,836 --> 00:08:59,126
It's right here. It's yours.

126
00:09:04,970 --> 00:09:06,430
I'm stamping this into your memory.

127
00:09:06,513 --> 00:09:09,523
I like it when you remember me
by Harvard, a nasty manager, and such,

128
00:09:09,599 --> 00:09:10,729
but...

129
00:09:11,852 --> 00:09:14,192
don't forget a man
who's smiling at you now.

130
00:09:26,449 --> 00:09:27,449
Yes.

131
00:09:30,704 --> 00:09:32,504
Remember these moments.

132
00:09:40,005 --> 00:09:41,795
It looks like
Sanchez will be coming home late.

133
00:09:43,091 --> 00:09:44,341
We should go to him.

134
00:09:57,564 --> 00:09:58,734
This is Hyeon-jung.

135
00:10:04,237 --> 00:10:06,697
After some man came into the hotel
as our guest,

136
00:10:07,032 --> 00:10:09,202
Ms. Choe didn't look so good.

137
00:10:09,284 --> 00:10:12,504
I found out that the guest was
the last son of the family

138
00:10:12,829 --> 00:10:14,329
that Ms. Choe loathes so much.

139
00:10:15,790 --> 00:10:17,960
She went to that man's funeral?

140
00:10:18,209 --> 00:10:19,089
Yes.

141
00:10:19,377 --> 00:10:21,627
Mr. Kim is really worried about her too.

142
00:10:22,005 --> 00:10:23,045
Ms. Jang.

143
00:10:23,673 --> 00:10:27,183
The incident that happened 42 years ago
won't happen again, right?

144
00:10:31,264 --> 00:10:33,734
What happened 42 years ago?

145
00:10:33,808 --> 00:10:36,558
The room service manager, Choe Seo-hui,

146
00:10:36,645 --> 00:10:39,555
left the hotel and almost became
an evil ghost that had to be eliminated.

147
00:10:40,315 --> 00:10:41,895
That level-headed Ms. Choe?

148
00:10:41,983 --> 00:10:45,363
Her daughter was the reason why
she loathes that family so much.

149
00:10:46,237 --> 00:10:48,407
And that darn family
messed with her daughter's grave.

150
00:10:50,951 --> 00:10:52,331
This is the site.

151
00:10:52,953 --> 00:10:56,833
The grave of a girl who passed away
on the 25th of this month

152
00:10:56,915 --> 00:10:59,205
is harming your family and your child.

153
00:10:59,292 --> 00:11:01,002
You must dig it out and get rid of it

154
00:11:01,169 --> 00:11:03,959
for your daughter-in-law
to give birth to a healthy baby

155
00:11:04,047 --> 00:11:05,917
who is in an inverted position now.

156
00:11:06,132 --> 00:11:10,392
You're not supposed to mess
with an old grave of a girl.

157
00:11:10,470 --> 00:11:12,390
My family line is about to run dry.

158
00:11:12,472 --> 00:11:13,972
Dig out the grave.

159
00:11:31,574 --> 00:11:33,034
<i>Stop it.</i>

160
00:11:34,035 --> 00:11:38,205
<i>Don't you dare touch my daughter's grave.</i>

161
00:11:42,711 --> 00:11:44,751
<i>I curse all of your family</i>

162
00:11:45,422 --> 00:11:47,762
<i>to die. All of you.</i>

163
00:11:50,385 --> 00:11:53,135
<i>I will make sure
your family line ends here.</i>

164
00:11:53,722 --> 00:11:56,222
<i>Die!</i>

165
00:12:06,609 --> 00:12:10,029
<i>If she had faced Mago
before the Grim Reaper got a hold of her,</i>

166
00:12:10,655 --> 00:12:12,775
<i>Ms. Choe would have ceased to exist.</i>

167
00:12:14,826 --> 00:12:17,866
That day, the Grim Reaper
and Ms. Jang worked out a nice deal,

168
00:12:17,954 --> 00:12:20,334
so Ms. Choe didn't get dragged
to the afterlife

169
00:12:20,415 --> 00:12:22,245
and could continue to work at the hotel.

170
00:12:23,626 --> 00:12:26,706
We made an offering of flowers
for ten months, right?

171
00:12:26,796 --> 00:12:27,916
It was for twelve months.

172
00:12:28,089 --> 00:12:29,129
Right.

173
00:12:29,215 --> 00:12:31,425
The flowers in the garden all wilted then.

174
00:12:31,551 --> 00:12:34,851
The manager before Ms. Hwang
lost all of Ms. Jang's money.

175
00:12:35,513 --> 00:12:37,683
We were the poorest then.

176
00:12:39,058 --> 00:12:40,638
You know what Ms. Jang did?

177
00:12:41,102 --> 00:12:45,022
Whenever I think about Ms. Jang
digging up arrowroots with a hoe...

178
00:12:47,358 --> 00:12:48,358
Hey.

179
00:12:48,568 --> 00:12:49,688
Don't think about it.

180
00:12:49,778 --> 00:12:50,648
Yes, ma'am.

181
00:12:50,904 --> 00:12:52,824
The son who was born 42 years ago

182
00:12:52,906 --> 00:12:54,696
died without having a son.

183
00:12:54,783 --> 00:12:57,493
Nothing will happen even if she meets
the people from that family

184
00:12:57,577 --> 00:12:58,747
at the funeral, right?

185
00:12:58,870 --> 00:13:01,460
What she's been wishing for
for 200 years is happening.

186
00:13:02,165 --> 00:13:03,415
I doubt anything will happen.

187
00:13:03,917 --> 00:13:07,957
Then, that means Ms. Choe will leave soon.

188
00:13:50,713 --> 00:13:51,923
Are you finished?

189
00:13:52,423 --> 00:13:55,053
The end has come to this family.

190
00:13:55,593 --> 00:13:59,313
I'll be able to leave without any regrets.

191
00:14:12,527 --> 00:14:13,697
You're here.

192
00:14:14,654 --> 00:14:18,074
Yes, he's the father of my baby.

193
00:14:19,409 --> 00:14:22,579
I thought I should at least
come to say goodbye.

194
00:14:27,375 --> 00:14:29,335
Didn't you say he was a bachelor?

195
00:14:30,003 --> 00:14:31,423
I guess

196
00:14:32,630 --> 00:14:33,880
he left an offspring.

197
00:14:34,632 --> 00:14:37,722
If the child in that woman's belly
is a boy,

198
00:14:38,720 --> 00:14:40,890
the Yeongju Yun family line

199
00:14:42,223 --> 00:14:44,563
will be carried on.

200
00:15:03,912 --> 00:15:08,042
I'm sorry I left my post unattended
without informing you.

201
00:15:17,550 --> 00:15:18,720
What happened?

202
00:15:18,927 --> 00:15:20,967
There's still one more child
in that family.

203
00:15:23,306 --> 00:15:24,556
Ms. Choe...

204
00:15:52,710 --> 00:15:54,800
Is there anyone inside?

205
00:15:55,213 --> 00:15:59,803
A baby is dying. Please open the door!

206
00:16:00,426 --> 00:16:04,006
Please open this door.

207
00:16:06,432 --> 00:16:08,772
Please open the door.

208
00:16:09,185 --> 00:16:12,605
No doctors will open their doors for you.

209
00:16:12,689 --> 00:16:14,319
That baby must not live.

210
00:16:14,399 --> 00:16:15,779
My baby...

211
00:16:17,402 --> 00:16:20,362
Please save my child.

212
00:16:47,974 --> 00:16:50,484
I asked the guest from the family

213
00:16:50,560 --> 00:16:52,850
and he said that a lover he broke up with
because of his parents

214
00:16:52,937 --> 00:16:54,647
is pregnant.

215
00:16:55,356 --> 00:16:57,606
That's why he couldn't go straight
to the afterlife.

216
00:16:58,276 --> 00:17:01,276
Ms. Choe must be disappointed.

217
00:17:01,738 --> 00:17:03,568
I feel sorry for that man,

218
00:17:03,656 --> 00:17:06,326
but no one can compare to Ms. Choe
who remained here for 200 years

219
00:17:06,409 --> 00:17:08,329
because of the sorrow of losing her child.

220
00:17:11,789 --> 00:17:13,669
I know the flower is withering.

221
00:17:19,797 --> 00:17:21,547
Can't it be stopped?

222
00:17:25,678 --> 00:17:28,308
I think Ms. Choe is more anxious
than anyone.

223
00:17:34,687 --> 00:17:36,017
I was really worried.

224
00:17:36,773 --> 00:17:38,983
Did you think I'd harm someone?

225
00:17:40,026 --> 00:17:41,936
I was worried you might get hurt.

226
00:17:43,905 --> 00:17:46,155
That's no concern of yours.

227
00:17:51,704 --> 00:17:53,794
Where did you get that strange suit?

228
00:17:57,210 --> 00:17:58,250
It's a tiger.

229
00:18:00,171 --> 00:18:03,011
Where did you find such a thing?

230
00:18:03,091 --> 00:18:05,511
I got it as a gift,
so I tried it on today.

231
00:18:05,927 --> 00:18:07,047
What do you think?

232
00:18:08,054 --> 00:18:10,774
You look funny. What on earth is that?

233
00:18:11,182 --> 00:18:12,852
Take it off already.

234
00:18:13,893 --> 00:18:16,403
I hear it's a brand name suit.

235
00:18:16,479 --> 00:18:18,059
Who cares if it's a brand name suit?

236
00:18:18,147 --> 00:18:20,017
You look like you are from the Serengeti.

237
00:18:20,108 --> 00:18:22,858
Does it look that strange?
I guess I shouldn't wear it outside.

238
00:18:22,944 --> 00:18:26,114
Of course not.
Even our dead guests will laugh at you.

239
00:18:27,490 --> 00:18:29,530
Should I wear it
when I see our guests off?

240
00:18:29,617 --> 00:18:30,947
They can laugh on their way out.

241
00:18:33,287 --> 00:18:36,077
Mr. Koo, you're bringing down
our hotel's class.

242
00:18:36,666 --> 00:18:40,086
Right. Did the guest
in Room 403 leave yet?

243
00:18:40,211 --> 00:18:41,921
I should see him out.

244
00:18:42,130 --> 00:18:44,760
He said he should see you before leaving.

245
00:18:45,216 --> 00:18:47,336
Let's head to the platform.

246
00:18:48,761 --> 00:18:50,641
You're not really going to wear that,
are you?

247
00:18:54,392 --> 00:18:55,982
Let's go together, Ms. Choe.

248
00:18:56,060 --> 00:18:57,270
Stay away from me.

249
00:18:58,020 --> 00:19:00,650
I think Mr. Koo decided to look funny

250
00:19:00,731 --> 00:19:04,611
to divert Ms. Choe from that family
and help her relax.

251
00:19:05,486 --> 00:19:07,526
He said he'd never wear it,

252
00:19:07,613 --> 00:19:09,533
but he's using it like this.

253
00:19:09,866 --> 00:19:10,906
Ms. Jang.

254
00:19:10,992 --> 00:19:14,622
I looked into why my matchmaking
for Mr. Koo didn't work out,

255
00:19:14,704 --> 00:19:17,464
and it turned out
his heart belonged to someone else.

256
00:19:18,791 --> 00:19:21,791
Someone who won the heart
of such a man must be happy.

257
00:19:22,211 --> 00:19:24,461
Yes. I'm happy.

258
00:19:25,173 --> 00:19:27,053
Why are you happy?

259
00:19:30,595 --> 00:19:33,425
Now that you know,
don't do something a crane would do.

260
00:19:33,514 --> 00:19:36,274
I'm calling you a crane because you hate
being called a birdbrain.

261
00:19:36,350 --> 00:19:38,020
Don't act like a crane.

262
00:19:38,352 --> 00:19:40,942
This must be a crane-like question,

263
00:19:41,147 --> 00:19:43,477
but do you also feel...

264
00:19:44,734 --> 00:19:47,454
You asked me
if we can't stop the flowers from falling.

265
00:19:48,738 --> 00:19:49,988
That's not possible.

266
00:19:51,574 --> 00:19:53,784
I wonder if it's because
I like him too much.

267
00:19:55,286 --> 00:19:57,156
I just can't seem to stop it.

268
00:19:59,749 --> 00:20:01,459
I feel sorry for you too, Mr. Kim.

269
00:20:02,793 --> 00:20:05,843
The flowers are falling because of love...

270
00:20:05,922 --> 00:20:07,972
Should I give you a glass of Tears?

271
00:20:10,051 --> 00:20:11,051
No.

272
00:20:12,261 --> 00:20:13,301
I don't like it.

273
00:20:14,680 --> 00:20:16,600
It tastes really bad.

274
00:20:23,231 --> 00:20:26,691
She's been consistently rude.

275
00:20:27,568 --> 00:20:29,448
How did he change her?

276
00:20:37,578 --> 00:20:38,618
Chan-sung.

277
00:20:40,331 --> 00:20:43,001
What is this?
Why did you get changed already?

278
00:20:43,459 --> 00:20:45,589
I was going to take a picture
of you in that suit.

279
00:20:46,254 --> 00:20:49,474
Thanks to you, I was able to use it well.

280
00:20:50,299 --> 00:20:51,929
But I don't want to leave a picture of it.

281
00:20:52,009 --> 00:20:53,969
Why not? It was totally my cup of tea.

282
00:20:54,053 --> 00:20:58,603
I'll buy you a zebra-print suit next time.

283
00:20:58,683 --> 00:21:01,983
Suit yourself. You can turn me
into a tiger or a zebra.

284
00:21:02,937 --> 00:21:04,107
You were really cool.

285
00:21:05,147 --> 00:21:06,817
The tiger in front of Ms. Choe

286
00:21:07,441 --> 00:21:09,531
was cooler than the Siberian tiger.

287
00:21:11,529 --> 00:21:15,319
Koo Chan-sung,
you're an excellent hotelier.

288
00:21:20,162 --> 00:21:21,502
I forgot

289
00:21:21,872 --> 00:21:24,462
that Ms. Choe was also a guest
who needed to be consoled

290
00:21:24,542 --> 00:21:26,712
in order for her to leave here.

291
00:21:29,964 --> 00:21:33,134
She's a long-term guest
with a deep-rooted resentment.

292
00:21:36,095 --> 00:21:39,515
Her resentment which is making her wait
to see the end of the Yun family

293
00:21:39,599 --> 00:21:41,059
might turn into a curse?

294
00:21:43,894 --> 00:21:46,694
Just as she wanted,
that family is facing a problem.

295
00:21:49,275 --> 00:21:51,565
I told you everything comes
with a price, right?

296
00:21:51,861 --> 00:21:54,321
For making her feel so much sorrow,

297
00:21:54,780 --> 00:21:56,870
they received a curse.

298
00:21:57,450 --> 00:21:59,160
But it's been 200 years already.

299
00:22:00,036 --> 00:22:03,156
Time doesn't mean anything to the dead.

300
00:22:04,206 --> 00:22:08,586
With such resentment,
one could spend 200 years,

301
00:22:09,086 --> 00:22:11,206
or 500 years,

302
00:22:13,883 --> 00:22:16,223
or even 1,000 years.

303
00:22:52,505 --> 00:22:55,085
<i>They wait for a long time</i>

304
00:22:55,716 --> 00:22:57,926
not knowing when their hearts
will open up again.

305
00:23:00,346 --> 00:23:02,306
I guess it could be considered
a curse too.

306
00:23:05,101 --> 00:23:06,191
Are you...

307
00:23:08,229 --> 00:23:10,399
still waiting for him to come?

308
00:23:12,733 --> 00:23:13,943
Chan-sung.

309
00:23:15,361 --> 00:23:16,741
If he comes,

310
00:23:18,697 --> 00:23:21,027
will you do what you did
for Ms. Choe for me too?

311
00:23:22,993 --> 00:23:24,583
Will you become a tiger?

312
00:23:28,916 --> 00:23:30,326
I told you to trust me.

313
00:23:31,043 --> 00:23:32,463
Anything is possible.

314
00:23:34,713 --> 00:23:36,093
Since I'm yours.

315
00:23:40,386 --> 00:23:41,386
Right.

316
00:23:42,638 --> 00:23:43,928
Then you wear that.

317
00:23:44,014 --> 00:23:46,854
And we will go to eat beef short rib soup
that tigers love.

318
00:23:47,309 --> 00:23:48,809
You said tigers like red bean porridge.

319
00:23:48,894 --> 00:23:49,854
Who said that?

320
00:23:49,937 --> 00:23:52,307
You did.
That tigers love red bean porridge.

321
00:23:53,232 --> 00:23:55,482
No tigers like red bean porridge.

322
00:23:55,568 --> 00:23:56,818
You think they're vegetarians?

323
00:23:56,902 --> 00:23:59,112
You have to get them some beef at least.

324
00:23:59,405 --> 00:24:02,485
All right. Let's go and have some soup.

325
00:24:07,705 --> 00:24:09,705
Let's put this on.

326
00:24:10,624 --> 00:24:11,674
I will not.

327
00:24:13,169 --> 00:24:16,799
If you don't wear this,
I will take all your clothes off.

328
00:24:17,381 --> 00:24:18,761
Do as you please.

329
00:24:22,094 --> 00:24:23,434
But will you be able to handle it?

330
00:24:26,182 --> 00:24:27,732
I don't think so.

331
00:24:34,565 --> 00:24:36,065
Let's have the soup tomorrow.

332
00:24:36,150 --> 00:24:39,110
I have to go home and see Sanchez.

333
00:24:42,865 --> 00:24:44,115
What are you doing?

334
00:24:45,159 --> 00:24:46,409
You don't have to know.

335
00:24:55,461 --> 00:24:57,841
They are flowers that fall
because of love.

336
00:24:58,380 --> 00:25:00,510
There are still so many flowers.

337
00:25:01,008 --> 00:25:03,048
It took more than 1,000 years
for them to bloom.

338
00:25:03,177 --> 00:25:04,927
I don't think they'll fall that easily.

339
00:25:07,515 --> 00:25:09,885
Look, it's a firefly.

340
00:25:12,186 --> 00:25:15,226
I saw it from time to time
after the tree changed.

341
00:25:16,190 --> 00:25:18,780
See? Even a firefly comes
now that the flowers have bloomed.

342
00:25:19,235 --> 00:25:21,895
But can something like that come in here?

343
00:25:22,738 --> 00:25:23,858
I don't know.

344
00:25:23,948 --> 00:25:27,118
Since it's inside the hotel,
it can't be alive.

345
00:25:27,993 --> 00:25:30,333
Is that what Mr. Koo was talking about?

346
00:25:31,288 --> 00:25:32,118
What?

347
00:25:32,206 --> 00:25:33,826
He asked me once

348
00:25:34,583 --> 00:25:37,043
if there could be a soul
that looks like a firefly.

349
00:25:38,087 --> 00:25:41,627
Why is there only one? It must be lonely.

350
00:27:13,432 --> 00:27:18,272
<i>He's spent all those years,
unable to show himself.</i>

351
00:27:18,354 --> 00:27:21,774
<i>He's always been with her like a dust.</i>

352
00:27:23,317 --> 00:27:25,527
<i>Now finally, he will be seen.</i>

353
00:27:32,951 --> 00:27:34,581
The flowers have finally bloomed.

354
00:27:34,995 --> 00:27:39,245
I wonder if she'll be willing to listen
to his side of the story.

355
00:27:45,214 --> 00:27:46,804
When things in one's heart are entangled,

356
00:27:47,091 --> 00:27:49,131
it's so hard to untangle them.

357
00:27:50,344 --> 00:27:52,014
I will weave them properly this time.

358
00:27:55,516 --> 00:27:58,596
I ate too much soup.

359
00:27:58,686 --> 00:28:00,226
I feel so bloated.

360
00:28:00,312 --> 00:28:03,072
I know that's just an excuse
to come here to see her.

361
00:28:07,111 --> 00:28:08,401
The baby she is carrying

362
00:28:08,487 --> 00:28:10,907
is the child of the family
Ms. Choe hates, right?

363
00:28:11,031 --> 00:28:13,531
Right. She thought the family line
finally ended.

364
00:28:13,617 --> 00:28:15,197
But it continues persistently.

365
00:28:15,285 --> 00:28:17,365
And that's the baby
who disappointed Ms. Choe.

366
00:28:18,831 --> 00:28:20,581
If only that child disappears,

367
00:28:20,874 --> 00:28:23,384
Ms. Choe's deep grudge will be resolved.

368
00:28:28,090 --> 00:28:29,430
Do you really think so?

369
00:28:32,511 --> 00:28:34,051
If the child disappears,

370
00:28:34,972 --> 00:28:36,142
will that solve everything?

371
00:28:38,976 --> 00:28:41,976
Shall I get rid of that baby right now?

372
00:28:43,439 --> 00:28:46,859
The baby doesn't seem to be
in good condition anyway.

373
00:28:57,244 --> 00:28:58,414
Are you all right?

374
00:29:00,372 --> 00:29:02,172
My stomach was tightening.

375
00:29:02,249 --> 00:29:04,749
You should be careful. I will help you.

376
00:29:09,465 --> 00:29:11,505
She is Ms. Choe's enemy.

377
00:29:12,634 --> 00:29:14,854
Why is he helping her?

378
00:29:20,434 --> 00:29:21,644
What is this?

379
00:29:23,604 --> 00:29:27,024
This is a nice car. I wanted to buy this.

380
00:29:27,107 --> 00:29:28,817
Just because you have an expensive car,

381
00:29:29,193 --> 00:29:30,943
doesn't mean you can park it anywhere.

382
00:29:34,948 --> 00:29:36,368
Isn't she also Mago?

383
00:29:36,450 --> 00:29:38,870
Oh, my! Mago!

384
00:29:38,952 --> 00:29:41,372
-Mago!
-Man-wol!

385
00:29:41,455 --> 00:29:43,995
It's been such a long time.

386
00:29:44,083 --> 00:29:46,673
You used to come to my hotel often
when Mun-suk was there.

387
00:29:46,752 --> 00:29:48,302
Why don't you come anymore?

388
00:29:48,378 --> 00:29:50,798
We don't get a lot of money
because you don't come.

389
00:29:51,340 --> 00:29:54,470
-Come more often.
-Where are you poking me?

390
00:29:54,927 --> 00:29:57,257
I'm very busy these days.

391
00:29:57,346 --> 00:29:59,716
I'm going to an opening now.

392
00:29:59,807 --> 00:30:01,597
I don't know where the place is,

393
00:30:01,683 --> 00:30:04,023
but it will be a success
thanks to your help.

394
00:30:04,103 --> 00:30:07,153
Some young people have started
a computer business

395
00:30:07,231 --> 00:30:09,361
in a small office here.

396
00:30:09,441 --> 00:30:12,441
-Computer business?
-Yes, computer business.

397
00:30:12,903 --> 00:30:15,953
I think it's praiseworthy
so I'm cheering them on.

398
00:30:16,073 --> 00:30:17,743
They are very lucky.

399
00:30:18,951 --> 00:30:21,501
And who are you?

400
00:30:21,578 --> 00:30:22,828
Is he the new manager?

401
00:30:22,913 --> 00:30:23,913
Yes.

402
00:30:25,624 --> 00:30:26,964
Nice to meet you.

403
00:30:29,169 --> 00:30:30,749
Take her hand quickly.
She'll bring you money.

404
00:30:33,715 --> 00:30:35,045
My name is Koo Chan-sung.

405
00:30:35,676 --> 00:30:37,006
You're holding it so hard.

406
00:30:38,345 --> 00:30:42,305
You seem very nice.
I think we'll be meeting often.

407
00:30:44,101 --> 00:30:46,651
Take good care of your guests.

408
00:30:46,728 --> 00:30:47,808
Especially,

409
00:30:48,522 --> 00:30:49,732
your first guest.

410
00:30:50,983 --> 00:30:52,193
"My first guest"?

411
00:30:52,276 --> 00:30:54,986
One's first guest is very important.

412
00:30:55,320 --> 00:30:59,530
That's why I'm going as their first guest
to support them.

413
00:31:00,784 --> 00:31:02,164
Man-wol.

414
00:31:03,120 --> 00:31:04,330
Goodbye.

415
00:31:05,956 --> 00:31:09,286
Have a good day. I've opened
lots of champagne bottles thanks to you.

416
00:31:10,460 --> 00:31:11,460
Right.

417
00:31:11,545 --> 00:31:14,915
By the way, you're so pretty nowadays.

418
00:31:22,347 --> 00:31:23,597
You will be rich.

419
00:31:23,682 --> 00:31:26,062
She's a deity of wealth.
She shook your hand and said nice things.

420
00:31:26,143 --> 00:31:29,103
Was that why you were
so excited to see her?

421
00:31:29,188 --> 00:31:32,478
Of course. I get excited whenever I meet
good-looking guys and rich women.

422
00:31:33,817 --> 00:31:35,817
Then you should treat me differently now.

423
00:31:38,447 --> 00:31:41,947
Since you'll be rich,
I'll treat you as a woman.

424
00:31:42,492 --> 00:31:43,872
Let's go, sister.

425
00:31:52,169 --> 00:31:53,419
First guest...

426
00:31:58,717 --> 00:32:02,467
There is a guest that even Ms. Jang
and the staff don't know about.

427
00:32:02,763 --> 00:32:06,603
Those who don't show their existence
also have the meaning of their existence.

428
00:32:06,683 --> 00:32:09,653
Letting them exist
in the way they want to exist

429
00:32:09,728 --> 00:32:11,648
is my answer to "the existence."

430
00:32:12,356 --> 00:32:14,146
Just say you don't know.

431
00:32:15,567 --> 00:32:18,487
By the way,
do you know where that murderer ghost is?

432
00:32:19,488 --> 00:32:21,868
It is not easy to find a vengeful ghost.

433
00:32:21,949 --> 00:32:23,739
You don't know that either.

434
00:32:23,825 --> 00:32:27,405
The seven guests who were murdered by him
think we will bring him in soon.

435
00:32:27,496 --> 00:32:29,866
They're waiting for him,
refusing to get on the bus.

436
00:32:37,506 --> 00:32:38,586
Tell them

437
00:32:39,007 --> 00:32:41,427
that they'll get to ride
a limousine if things get delayed.

438
00:32:41,510 --> 00:32:44,010
I guess that means
it's going to take some time.

439
00:32:44,763 --> 00:32:46,143
Vengeful ghosts...

440
00:32:47,140 --> 00:32:49,810
always hide themselves in darkness.

441
00:33:01,488 --> 00:33:04,738
<i>If something's dark
even when it's no place for a shadow,</i>

442
00:33:05,242 --> 00:33:07,122
<i>that's where they'll be.</i>

443
00:33:11,790 --> 00:33:13,710
Don't be late for the movie.

444
00:33:13,792 --> 00:33:16,552
If you're going to be late again,
don't come. Let's just break up.

445
00:33:19,131 --> 00:33:22,261
<i>If you think you're being watched
by someone from a dark space,</i>

446
00:33:22,801 --> 00:33:23,931
<i>it's one of them.</i>

447
00:34:20,108 --> 00:34:22,238
Hello, Sanchez.

448
00:34:48,178 --> 00:34:49,388
VERONICA

449
00:35:13,203 --> 00:35:15,583
<i>I was so close to catching him.</i>

450
00:35:17,374 --> 00:35:20,254
He doesn't approach Koo Chan-sung
because you're always with him.

451
00:35:20,335 --> 00:35:22,745
It seems like he's aiming
for people around Chan-sung.

452
00:35:23,463 --> 00:35:25,763
I'm sure I'll catch him soon,
but he should warn them

453
00:35:26,216 --> 00:35:27,426
just in case.

454
00:35:28,635 --> 00:35:32,055
Mr. Kim, does Yu-na still
hang around with Hyeon-jung?

455
00:35:32,139 --> 00:35:33,809
She's with him even right now.

456
00:35:42,983 --> 00:35:44,233
-That's good.
-Okay.

457
00:35:45,360 --> 00:35:47,360
-I did well, didn't I?
-Yes, you did well.

458
00:35:47,446 --> 00:35:48,446
I know, right?

459
00:35:56,913 --> 00:35:57,913
My goodness.

460
00:35:58,999 --> 00:35:59,999
Man-wol.

461
00:36:00,876 --> 00:36:03,876
I heard you got hurt.
I brought you some medicine.

462
00:36:05,672 --> 00:36:06,512
Thanks.

463
00:36:08,049 --> 00:36:10,889
How did you know I got hurt?
I didn't even tell Chan-sung.

464
00:36:11,386 --> 00:36:12,546
I have an informant.

465
00:36:12,637 --> 00:36:13,677
Who?

466
00:36:15,348 --> 00:36:16,428
The Grim Reaper.

467
00:36:18,768 --> 00:36:21,728
I guess you also have connections
with the Grim Reaper.

468
00:36:21,813 --> 00:36:24,613
I didn't know I was friends
with such an incredible being.

469
00:36:25,567 --> 00:36:26,987
Light this up at home.

470
00:36:29,321 --> 00:36:32,241
Keep it nice and bright,
and don't go anywhere dark for a while.

471
00:36:32,324 --> 00:36:33,664
I guess I didn't get hurt

472
00:36:33,742 --> 00:36:35,832
merely because of bad luck.

473
00:36:37,537 --> 00:36:41,537
I've been to your hotel.
There's nothing I can't believe now.

474
00:36:41,875 --> 00:36:43,205
I'll do as you say.

475
00:36:44,586 --> 00:36:45,586
Thank you.

476
00:36:50,175 --> 00:36:51,295
I'm sorry.

477
00:36:53,637 --> 00:36:56,847
I should've been nice to you then
instead of being so sarcastic.

478
00:36:57,516 --> 00:36:58,926
I didn't really think

479
00:36:59,893 --> 00:37:02,943
you'd be able to give that pizza
to Veronica.

480
00:37:03,688 --> 00:37:05,938
I just wanted to believe
that it's possible.

481
00:37:14,157 --> 00:37:17,537
Sanchez, you're Chan-sung's best friend,
aren't you?

482
00:37:20,205 --> 00:37:21,535
If...

483
00:37:23,416 --> 00:37:24,706
Chan-sung

484
00:37:25,377 --> 00:37:28,337
also goes through the same thing someday,

485
00:37:29,422 --> 00:37:31,422
I hope you'll be there to console him.

486
00:37:39,140 --> 00:37:42,190
I'll be off now.
There are a lot of guests at the hotel.

487
00:37:42,936 --> 00:37:44,646
You should light up the incense
in every room.

488
00:37:44,729 --> 00:37:46,569
In every single room?

489
00:37:46,898 --> 00:37:49,358
I guess I should tell Mi-ra
to light one up in her room as well.

490
00:37:52,445 --> 00:37:54,605
I forgot she lived here.

491
00:37:55,574 --> 00:37:58,874
Sanchez, is Mi-ra also acquainted

492
00:37:58,952 --> 00:38:00,622
with Seol Ji-won?

493
00:38:00,954 --> 00:38:03,504
Yes, they met in the States.
Why do you ask?

494
00:38:05,709 --> 00:38:07,129
Where is she right now?

495
00:38:07,460 --> 00:38:08,800
Mi-ra has a boyfriend.

496
00:38:08,878 --> 00:38:11,008
She went to the movie theater
with her boyfriend.

497
00:38:11,756 --> 00:38:12,966
The movie theater?

498
00:38:14,050 --> 00:38:16,180
She's just friends with Chan-sung now.

499
00:38:16,261 --> 00:38:18,011
Mi-ra's boyfriend is really good-looking.

500
00:38:18,096 --> 00:38:20,096
Would you like to see a photo?
Wait a second.

501
00:38:26,521 --> 00:38:30,361
Movie theaters are really dark.

502
00:38:33,028 --> 00:38:34,068
Why should I care?

503
00:38:37,240 --> 00:38:38,330
Man-wol, look...

504
00:38:42,370 --> 00:38:43,660
She's gone already.

505
00:38:44,289 --> 00:38:46,169
I guess she doesn't walk
like normal people.

506
00:38:48,376 --> 00:38:52,376
Mi-ra would've been in big trouble
if she didn't have a boyfriend.

507
00:38:58,470 --> 00:39:00,220
Yeong-su, when are you coming?

508
00:39:00,305 --> 00:39:01,845
The movie's going to start soon.

509
00:39:02,474 --> 00:39:04,274
Stop making excuses.

510
00:39:07,520 --> 00:39:09,860
Okay, hurry up.

511
00:39:15,028 --> 00:39:17,608
I guess that vengeful ghost
will take care of her for me.

512
00:39:31,503 --> 00:39:32,673
What are you doing?

513
00:39:33,463 --> 00:39:34,633
Where have you been?

514
00:39:36,341 --> 00:39:37,341
What?

515
00:39:38,760 --> 00:39:40,680
I went to apologize to Sanchez.

516
00:39:40,929 --> 00:39:42,969
You went by yourself?
You should've taken me with you.

517
00:39:43,056 --> 00:39:44,596
I just wanted to get it over with.

518
00:39:46,184 --> 00:39:47,234
You've become a nice person.

519
00:39:47,394 --> 00:39:48,444
Not really.

520
00:39:49,145 --> 00:39:51,935
Thank you for caring about my friend.

521
00:39:52,148 --> 00:39:53,608
You really did become a nice person.

522
00:39:54,401 --> 00:39:55,441
Chan-sung.

523
00:39:55,944 --> 00:39:59,364
You made me bloom flowers.
You've changed me a lot.

524
00:39:59,864 --> 00:40:01,574
But you can't change my roots.

525
00:40:01,908 --> 00:40:03,328
Don't even dream of it.

526
00:40:03,410 --> 00:40:06,580
Do I need to get in your way again?

527
00:40:06,663 --> 00:40:09,833
No, I didn't do anything.

528
00:40:10,125 --> 00:40:11,205
I'm not lying.

529
00:40:11,292 --> 00:40:14,302
So if anything happens,
it's not because of me.

530
00:40:16,047 --> 00:40:18,087
We have a lot of guests today,
so I'm quite busy.

531
00:40:18,174 --> 00:40:21,054
I'll drop by after I'm done with work.
See you then.

532
00:40:30,228 --> 00:40:31,398
Darn.

533
00:41:01,009 --> 00:41:02,179
Su-jin!

534
00:41:14,689 --> 00:41:17,029
Sir, I noticed that you went outside.

535
00:41:17,108 --> 00:41:19,688
-You can't just go outside--
-Please help me.

536
00:41:20,945 --> 00:41:24,445
I heard this hotel has a human manager
who helps out with human affairs.

537
00:41:25,158 --> 00:41:26,328
What's going on?

538
00:41:26,409 --> 00:41:29,329
My girlfriend's sick right now,
but no one's there to help her.

539
00:41:29,746 --> 00:41:32,326
If no one helps her,
my child will be in danger.

540
00:41:35,543 --> 00:41:37,553
You should go back to your room.

541
00:41:38,129 --> 00:41:39,169
I will

542
00:41:40,006 --> 00:41:42,426
take the manager there and help her out.

543
00:41:45,470 --> 00:41:46,550
Thank you.

544
00:42:06,449 --> 00:42:08,659
I'm not going to call Mr. Koo.

545
00:42:08,868 --> 00:42:11,828
I'm going to do nothing
and watch their family line end.

546
00:42:13,665 --> 00:42:16,375
You can do whatever you want.
I don't intend to stop you.

547
00:42:18,127 --> 00:42:20,547
I guess it's finally going
to come to an end.

548
00:42:20,839 --> 00:42:23,049
How about you witness

549
00:42:24,259 --> 00:42:26,049
how their family line ends?

550
00:42:29,681 --> 00:42:31,101
I know where she is.

551
00:42:31,808 --> 00:42:33,638
You just need to go there and watch.

552
00:42:34,060 --> 00:42:35,690
You don't need to do anything.

553
00:42:41,818 --> 00:42:43,528
Someone once told me

554
00:42:44,070 --> 00:42:45,490
that seeing it

555
00:42:46,322 --> 00:42:48,282
won't resolve my resentment.

556
00:42:53,079 --> 00:42:54,619
I want you to prove

557
00:42:56,082 --> 00:42:58,502
that they're wrong.

558
00:43:22,483 --> 00:43:24,573
My baby...

559
00:43:30,408 --> 00:43:32,408
My baby...

560
00:43:36,497 --> 00:43:37,537
<i>My baby...</i>

561
00:43:39,334 --> 00:43:40,384
<i>My baby...</i>

562
00:43:48,718 --> 00:43:50,548
My baby...

563
00:43:52,472 --> 00:43:54,562
My baby...

564
00:44:15,328 --> 00:44:17,118
Please tell Mr. Koo

565
00:44:19,499 --> 00:44:21,289
that this woman is in danger.

566
00:44:35,223 --> 00:44:38,773
911 EMERGENCY SERVICE

567
00:44:49,070 --> 00:44:51,410
Ms. Choe, the woman was taken

568
00:44:51,489 --> 00:44:53,319
to a hospital quickly by ambulance.

569
00:44:53,616 --> 00:44:55,616
The mother and baby

570
00:44:56,369 --> 00:44:57,499
are both okay.

571
00:45:09,590 --> 00:45:10,720
I was

572
00:45:11,634 --> 00:45:13,934
married to the eldest son
of the Yun family.

573
00:45:14,637 --> 00:45:18,427
I wasn't able to bear a child
until I was quite old.

574
00:45:21,102 --> 00:45:23,812
The child I finally gave birth to...

575
00:45:26,482 --> 00:45:27,782
was a girl.

576
00:45:44,751 --> 00:45:45,841
No.

577
00:45:49,672 --> 00:45:52,132
<i>My husband had to use
someone else's stomach</i>

578
00:45:52,216 --> 00:45:54,796
<i>to bear a son who would
carry on the family name.</i>

579
00:45:55,511 --> 00:45:58,561
<i>I had to leave my newborn daughter behind</i>

580
00:45:58,639 --> 00:46:01,679
<i>to go pray at a famous temple</i>

581
00:46:01,976 --> 00:46:06,056
<i>for the child in that woman's stomach
to be a son.</i>

582
00:46:07,648 --> 00:46:08,778
<i>But...</i>

583
00:46:09,734 --> 00:46:12,784
To make sure
the child in her belly is a boy,

584
00:46:13,029 --> 00:46:15,659
you need to get rid of the girl
that was born earlier.

585
00:46:16,073 --> 00:46:17,533
According to my fortune-telling,

586
00:46:17,617 --> 00:46:21,327
that girl is getting in the way
of all the men in this family.

587
00:46:21,913 --> 00:46:24,543
If a family has a girl
with such a bad fortune,

588
00:46:24,624 --> 00:46:28,004
that family will never give birth
to any boys.

589
00:46:34,300 --> 00:46:39,010
<i>My baby didn't get any water for days.</i>

590
00:46:39,388 --> 00:46:41,178
<i>They didn't even change her diapers.</i>

591
00:46:41,265 --> 00:46:43,015
<i>She was neglected like that.</i>

592
00:46:43,768 --> 00:46:46,768
<i>By the time I ran over to her
after hearing about that,</i>

593
00:46:47,438 --> 00:46:50,108
<i>the child was close to death.</i>

594
00:46:50,983 --> 00:46:53,743
Please open the door.

595
00:46:53,820 --> 00:46:55,610
My baby is dying.

596
00:46:55,696 --> 00:46:57,366
Is there anyone inside?

597
00:46:58,866 --> 00:47:01,406
Please open the door!

598
00:47:01,494 --> 00:47:04,874
No doctors will open their doors for you.

599
00:47:04,956 --> 00:47:07,076
That baby must not live.

600
00:47:08,709 --> 00:47:11,129
My baby...

601
00:47:12,171 --> 00:47:14,131
<i>My child died,</i>

602
00:47:14,590 --> 00:47:16,760
<i>but there was nothing I could do.</i>

603
00:47:17,051 --> 00:47:18,221
There, there.

604
00:47:18,302 --> 00:47:20,812
<i>I started to lose my mind.</i>

605
00:47:23,683 --> 00:47:25,893
Their family will dry up.

606
00:47:26,477 --> 00:47:30,397
She used to be clean and tidy.
What happened to her?

607
00:47:30,648 --> 00:47:34,148
That Yun family was too harsh on her.

608
00:47:34,235 --> 00:47:36,895
How could they turn someone like that?

609
00:47:46,205 --> 00:47:48,915
Don't touch her!

610
00:47:49,000 --> 00:47:51,500
Don't touch my baby!

611
00:47:51,586 --> 00:47:54,046
Don't touch her!

612
00:47:54,338 --> 00:47:56,338
Don't touch my baby!

613
00:48:08,853 --> 00:48:11,023
The Yun family

614
00:48:11,606 --> 00:48:13,606
will die out.

615
00:48:14,984 --> 00:48:16,494
Even after I die,

616
00:48:17,069 --> 00:48:19,859
I'll watch that happen.

617
00:48:22,658 --> 00:48:24,538
I'll make sure...

618
00:48:42,887 --> 00:48:45,677
That's how I swore I'd get my revenge.

619
00:48:50,478 --> 00:48:52,648
But earlier, I couldn't bear to watch

620
00:48:54,190 --> 00:48:56,650
that baby die until the end.

621
00:50:03,259 --> 00:50:06,299
<i>If the child disappears,
will that solve everything?</i>

622
00:50:08,264 --> 00:50:09,644
<i>Do you really think so?</i>

623
00:50:23,988 --> 00:50:25,318
YEONG-SU

624
00:50:25,489 --> 00:50:28,449
<i>I'm running a little late.
Go ahead and watch it. I'll go in later.</i>

625
00:50:30,161 --> 00:50:31,291
POWER OFF

626
00:51:03,778 --> 00:51:05,278
What you said was right.

627
00:51:08,449 --> 00:51:11,329
I was wrong, so I'll tell you something.

628
00:51:12,411 --> 00:51:13,661
Your friend...

629
00:51:17,208 --> 00:51:19,088
Lee Mi-ra might be in danger.

630
00:51:27,134 --> 00:51:28,304
Her phone is turned off.

631
00:51:28,594 --> 00:51:30,354
This has to be the closest theater
to our house.

632
00:51:30,512 --> 00:51:32,932
Don't be so dramatic.

633
00:51:33,056 --> 00:51:36,016
That vengeful ghost won't be
strong enough to kill someone.

634
00:51:36,101 --> 00:51:40,021
At most, she'll get a burn or a cut.

635
00:51:40,147 --> 00:51:42,727
Did you keep this to yourself
so you could see Mi-ra get hurt?

636
00:51:42,941 --> 00:51:44,401
Then why are you telling me now?

637
00:51:49,406 --> 00:51:53,076
Did you change your mind
after watching Ms. Choe?

638
00:51:53,452 --> 00:51:56,122
Yes. My heart is shaking.

639
00:51:56,747 --> 00:51:57,827
Chan-sung.

640
00:51:59,708 --> 00:52:00,668
Mi-ra.

641
00:52:01,084 --> 00:52:03,004
What is this? Are you two here
to watch a movie?

642
00:52:03,545 --> 00:52:04,455
What about you?

643
00:52:04,546 --> 00:52:06,756
How darn lucky.

644
00:52:07,507 --> 00:52:09,217
I got stood up.

645
00:52:09,343 --> 00:52:12,013
I felt too offended
to sit there alone, so I left.

646
00:52:12,346 --> 00:52:15,096
I guess he didn't come here.
Thank goodness.

647
00:52:15,182 --> 00:52:17,062
What are you saying?

648
00:52:17,142 --> 00:52:19,352
I was mad
because my boyfriend didn't show up,

649
00:52:19,436 --> 00:52:23,066
then a pervert behind me went, "Hello."

650
00:52:26,777 --> 00:52:28,947
I guess he did come after all.

651
00:52:30,364 --> 00:52:32,624
What about Yeong-su?
Are you sure he didn't come here?

652
00:53:42,811 --> 00:53:44,231
Are you looking for me?

653
00:53:48,191 --> 00:53:49,571
This is interesting.

654
00:53:50,610 --> 00:53:52,030
Keep looking for me.

655
00:54:08,879 --> 00:54:09,879
Yeon-u.

656
00:54:09,963 --> 00:54:11,263
Yeong-su!

657
00:54:14,885 --> 00:54:17,385
Yeong-su, are you okay? Get up.

658
00:54:17,471 --> 00:54:18,761
Yeong-su.

659
00:54:21,016 --> 00:54:22,266
Yeong-su.

660
00:54:23,018 --> 00:54:25,348
Are you okay?

661
00:54:30,108 --> 00:54:31,778
Are you okay, Yeong-su?

662
00:54:32,235 --> 00:54:33,395
I'm fine.

663
00:54:33,862 --> 00:54:36,952
I work out on a regular basis,
so this is not a problem.

664
00:54:37,199 --> 00:54:39,529
I'm glad nothing broke.

665
00:54:39,618 --> 00:54:42,248
I got a good rest thanks to you.
I'll get going now.

666
00:54:43,079 --> 00:54:44,079
No.

667
00:54:45,081 --> 00:54:48,081
You can rest a little longer. Relax.

668
00:54:48,919 --> 00:54:50,379
This is Chan-sung's room.

669
00:54:50,462 --> 00:54:53,052
This is the cleanest room in our house.

670
00:54:53,131 --> 00:54:54,881
Mi-ra, this is not "our" house.

671
00:54:54,966 --> 00:54:56,926
That would mean your room is
extremely dirty.

672
00:54:57,010 --> 00:54:59,100
Yeong-su, how are your teeth?

673
00:54:59,179 --> 00:55:01,889
What about your tongue?
Did you not bite it?

674
00:55:02,140 --> 00:55:03,560
I'm fine, Mi-ra.

675
00:55:04,851 --> 00:55:06,941
Sanchez, go get some more ice water.

676
00:55:10,065 --> 00:55:10,935
Okay.

677
00:55:17,906 --> 00:55:19,316
Should I check your face?

678
00:55:19,699 --> 00:55:21,369
-Let me see.
-I told you, I'm fine.

679
00:55:21,451 --> 00:55:22,791
What about your back?

680
00:55:23,370 --> 00:55:24,960
What is it? What's wrong?

681
00:55:25,038 --> 00:55:26,668
That part hurts the most.

682
00:55:26,748 --> 00:55:29,208
-Really? What about the other side?
-That side too.

683
00:55:37,467 --> 00:55:39,337
<i>How are Yeon-u and Song-hwa</i>

684
00:55:40,679 --> 00:55:42,429
together?

685
00:55:42,806 --> 00:55:44,516
He's not Yeon-u. He's Park Yeong-su.

686
00:55:44,599 --> 00:55:46,309
And she's not Song-hwa. She's Lee Mi-ra.

687
00:55:48,395 --> 00:55:50,105
The two of them are dating.

688
00:55:50,689 --> 00:55:52,899
I met Yeong-su through Mi-ra.

689
00:55:56,194 --> 00:55:58,364
I thought it might make things
complicated for you,

690
00:55:59,364 --> 00:56:01,204
so I didn't tell you about them.

691
00:56:01,992 --> 00:56:03,662
Because they're the people you despise

692
00:56:05,120 --> 00:56:06,960
and care dearly for.

693
00:56:17,090 --> 00:56:20,180
<i>To you, she may be an object
of an unresolved grudge.</i>

694
00:56:20,510 --> 00:56:21,930
<i>To her,</i>

695
00:56:22,262 --> 00:56:25,392
<i>you're a piece of her previous lives
that she doesn't even remember.</i>

696
00:56:26,349 --> 00:56:28,479
<i>Just let her pass by.</i>

697
00:57:10,268 --> 00:57:11,848
Are you feeling confused?

698
00:57:13,897 --> 00:57:17,727
The person I cared dearly for and
the person I hated the most are dating.

699
00:57:18,610 --> 00:57:22,070
Killing a person I wish to kill
won't relieve my resentment.

700
00:57:25,575 --> 00:57:27,075
Were you not able

701
00:57:28,662 --> 00:57:30,622
to kill him then?

702
00:57:34,042 --> 00:57:35,212
He died.

703
00:57:37,921 --> 00:57:39,591
He died that day.

704
00:58:50,952 --> 00:58:52,792
You survived.

705
00:58:54,914 --> 00:58:56,504
I survived

706
00:58:57,667 --> 00:59:00,497
to keep my promise to kill you.

707
00:59:03,631 --> 00:59:05,091
I'm proud of you,

708
00:59:06,426 --> 00:59:07,636
Man-wol.

709
00:59:16,478 --> 00:59:19,438
FULL MOON

710
00:59:19,939 --> 00:59:21,979
You memorized the letters well.

711
00:59:25,820 --> 00:59:27,610
Did Yeon-u engrave it for you?

712
00:59:32,619 --> 00:59:34,699
He was dexterous indeed.

713
00:59:38,917 --> 00:59:40,497
I guess the blade of this sword...

714
00:59:42,587 --> 00:59:44,587
carries Yeon-u's grudges too.

715
00:59:48,593 --> 00:59:50,933
There are many who have grudges
against you.

716
00:59:53,390 --> 00:59:55,520
You need to learn of them all,

717
00:59:55,975 --> 00:59:58,895
and die in pain and misery.

718
01:00:04,567 --> 01:00:06,437
What about ours?

719
01:00:10,365 --> 01:00:12,775
I'm just happy to see you again.

720
01:00:22,127 --> 01:00:25,047
As a beautiful bride,
you would welcome me,

721
01:00:27,674 --> 01:00:29,474
and I'd say that I missed you

722
01:00:30,760 --> 01:00:32,720
while stroking your face.

723
01:00:37,725 --> 01:00:38,805
Shut your mouth.

724
01:00:51,990 --> 01:00:53,910
FULL MOON

725
01:01:30,612 --> 01:01:31,912
This is...

726
01:01:34,741 --> 01:01:37,041
the end for us.

727
01:02:28,169 --> 01:02:31,169
I won't let your people survive.

728
01:02:32,799 --> 01:02:35,129
I'm going to burn down this castle.

729
01:02:36,636 --> 01:02:38,806
Our last moment together

730
01:02:39,597 --> 01:02:41,057
is this.

731
01:02:43,977 --> 01:02:46,807
You have to die after seeing all of that.

732
01:02:52,151 --> 01:02:53,531
Man-wol.

733
01:02:55,947 --> 01:02:58,197
I'll keep you in my heart

734
01:03:00,410 --> 01:03:02,790
and become the moon that never falls...

735
01:03:05,540 --> 01:03:07,000
to watch you from afar.

736
01:04:06,434 --> 01:04:10,904
<i>After he died that day,
I was blinded by my desire to get revenge</i>

737
01:04:11,272 --> 01:04:13,652
<i>and killed a lot of people.</i>

738
01:04:15,985 --> 01:04:20,025
<i>Then I put my people's belongings
in a coffin and searched everywhere</i>

739
01:04:20,948 --> 01:04:23,158
<i>to find the Guest House of the Moon.</i>

740
01:04:27,413 --> 01:04:31,213
<i>I killed whoever got in my way.</i>

741
01:04:32,794 --> 01:04:35,514
<i>When I finally arrived
at the Guest House of the Moon,</i>

742
01:04:36,422 --> 01:04:37,802
<i>what I faced</i>

743
01:04:38,800 --> 01:04:40,800
<i>was myself covered in blood.</i>

744
01:04:53,147 --> 01:04:56,187
My sins are heavy,
and my grudges are deep.

745
01:04:59,237 --> 01:05:01,277
That's the real me.

746
01:05:08,329 --> 01:05:09,459
I have...

747
01:05:11,791 --> 01:05:14,291
waited for the man for so long,

748
01:05:16,170 --> 01:05:17,510
planning to vanish

749
01:05:18,256 --> 01:05:20,216
after bringing him down with me

750
01:05:21,008 --> 01:05:22,798
to the rock bottom.

751
01:05:33,730 --> 01:05:35,360
I came to you instead.

752
01:05:39,819 --> 01:05:40,819
I...

753
01:05:42,196 --> 01:05:43,986
cannot make you

754
01:05:44,532 --> 01:05:46,622
forget your painful memories,

755
01:05:47,618 --> 01:05:49,698
but I want to lift you out of them.

756
01:06:58,231 --> 01:07:01,111
Does this bus go to Myeong-dong, sir?

757
01:07:01,192 --> 01:07:02,442
Yes, it does.

758
01:07:02,985 --> 01:07:05,275
Are you alone? Where's your mom?

759
01:07:05,530 --> 01:07:06,990
I'm going to meet my mom.

760
01:07:07,156 --> 01:07:10,616
Do you know about Hotel del Luna
in Myeong-dong?

761
01:07:10,827 --> 01:07:13,157
That's where my mom is.

762
01:07:24,549 --> 01:07:28,049
Ms. Choe!

763
01:07:32,682 --> 01:07:34,062
Are you leaving now?

764
01:07:35,101 --> 01:07:36,641
How could you not even say goodbye?

765
01:07:36,727 --> 01:07:38,937
We've been working together
for the last 200 years!

766
01:07:43,150 --> 01:07:44,400
I'm hurt.

767
01:07:47,572 --> 01:07:48,742
I'm not leaving.

768
01:07:49,323 --> 01:07:52,333
I was only cleaning the car
because the Grim Reaper asked me to.

769
01:07:54,912 --> 01:07:56,002
Is that right?

770
01:07:58,499 --> 01:08:02,549
Why does he always ask you
to clean the car? It's not our job.

771
01:08:02,670 --> 01:08:03,800
I'm done.

772
01:08:07,383 --> 01:08:08,593
Are you not leaving then?

773
01:08:08,676 --> 01:08:10,886
I don't even know
if the child is a boy or a girl.

774
01:08:10,970 --> 01:08:12,140
I have to see that first.

775
01:08:13,055 --> 01:08:15,595
I ran all the way over here for nothing.

776
01:08:15,766 --> 01:08:17,056
Mr. Kim,

777
01:08:19,478 --> 01:08:22,518
please make me the Tears.

778
01:08:22,607 --> 01:08:23,647
A strong one, please.

779
01:08:23,733 --> 01:08:25,483
Sure. Let's go.

780
01:08:27,653 --> 01:08:30,163
-Did you cry?
-No.

781
01:08:30,489 --> 01:08:33,659
-That's a tear.
-I told you I didn't.

782
01:08:33,743 --> 01:08:35,623
-I think it is.
-No.

783
01:08:35,828 --> 01:08:38,208
Be good to me while you have the chance.

784
01:08:38,789 --> 01:08:40,039
I will.

785
01:08:41,667 --> 01:08:44,797
I hid a present for you in here.

786
01:08:44,879 --> 01:08:46,549
Find it. You have one chance.

787
01:08:46,631 --> 01:08:48,381
How can I do that in one try?

788
01:08:48,758 --> 01:08:49,968
I'll give you a hint.

789
01:08:50,134 --> 01:08:51,304
Sure.

790
01:08:53,179 --> 01:08:57,179
The room number is the same
as the day we first met.

791
01:08:57,934 --> 01:08:59,854
-The day we first met?
-Yes.

792
01:09:01,687 --> 01:09:03,857
How am I supposed to remember that?

793
01:09:05,524 --> 01:09:07,194
How can you not?

794
01:09:08,903 --> 01:09:11,243
Do you not remember the date
of our first kiss either?

795
01:09:11,322 --> 01:09:14,082
Don't say it out too loud.

796
01:09:14,992 --> 01:09:17,242
Only ghosts will hear us anyway.

797
01:09:17,536 --> 01:09:20,366
Think harder. When did we first meet?

798
01:09:21,123 --> 01:09:25,803
It was when flowers were blooming,

799
01:09:26,837 --> 01:09:28,707
-so maybe June?
-June?

800
01:09:28,798 --> 01:09:30,968
-No, that's not right.
-June?

801
01:09:31,050 --> 01:09:33,640
-Maybe May?
-Which day in May?

802
01:09:33,719 --> 01:09:37,259
-May...
-Which day? Tell me.

803
01:09:37,348 --> 01:09:40,978
-It's not May 5th, is it?
-May 5th?

804
01:09:41,060 --> 01:09:42,350
I know that's wrong.

805
01:09:52,446 --> 01:09:53,776
It's a child.

806
01:09:54,240 --> 01:09:56,740
We rarely see a child come here alone.

807
01:10:00,955 --> 01:10:03,455
Are you here alone?

808
01:10:03,541 --> 01:10:05,841
Yes. I'm here to see my mom.

809
01:10:06,168 --> 01:10:09,958
Did you follow your mom here?

810
01:10:15,094 --> 01:10:17,434
You are not dead...

811
01:10:20,975 --> 01:10:22,555
He's alive.

812
01:10:30,735 --> 01:10:32,605
You saw this place in your dream, you say?

813
01:10:32,695 --> 01:10:35,025
Mom said that she was all good here.

814
01:10:37,033 --> 01:10:39,413
It's a side effect of a dream call.

815
01:10:40,244 --> 01:10:44,254
There's a living child in here,
looking for his dead mom.

816
01:10:44,331 --> 01:10:46,291
Please take him home safely.

817
01:10:47,293 --> 01:10:49,633
Is his mom still here?

818
01:10:49,712 --> 01:10:52,342
She already left for the afterlife
yesterday.

819
01:10:52,423 --> 01:10:55,183
Please talk to the child
and get him out of here.

820
01:11:02,433 --> 01:11:03,643
Where did he go?

821
01:11:10,357 --> 01:11:11,607
Where's the child?

822
01:11:11,692 --> 01:11:13,862
You were the one watching him.

823
01:11:13,944 --> 01:11:16,324
I went to bring some ice cream for him.

824
01:11:16,906 --> 01:11:19,576
We have to find him. Let's split.

825
01:11:20,409 --> 01:11:21,449
My goodness.

826
01:11:22,661 --> 01:11:23,661
Hey, kid.

827
01:11:24,330 --> 01:11:25,920
Where could he have gone?

828
01:11:26,290 --> 01:11:28,630
Hey, kid.

829
01:11:31,295 --> 01:11:32,245
Hey, kid.

830
01:11:34,715 --> 01:11:35,795
Hey, kid.

831
01:11:39,512 --> 01:11:42,722
Hello, have you seen
a little child around here?

832
01:11:42,807 --> 01:11:46,477
The kid? I saw him heading
to the platform.

833
01:11:48,521 --> 01:11:49,521
What?

834
01:12:00,783 --> 01:12:01,833
Hold on!

835
01:12:27,768 --> 01:12:32,228
THE SAMDO RIVER

836
01:12:32,314 --> 01:12:36,364
THIS WORLD, THE AFTERLIFE

837
01:12:37,611 --> 01:12:40,241
What? A living kid came in here?

838
01:12:40,322 --> 01:12:43,412
Yes. He disappeared,
so we're looking for him right now.

839
01:12:43,909 --> 01:12:45,999
How could the front desk not catch him?

840
01:13:02,887 --> 01:13:04,507
Was this tunnel always so long?

841
01:13:27,286 --> 01:13:29,076
Am I trapped?

842
01:13:40,090 --> 01:13:41,130
I found him!

843
01:13:41,675 --> 01:13:43,085
I found him.

844
01:13:44,053 --> 01:13:45,803
He was in front of the platform.

845
01:13:45,888 --> 01:13:47,678
We could've been in serious trouble.

846
01:13:48,557 --> 01:13:50,427
Bring Hyeon-jung here

847
01:13:50,851 --> 01:13:52,651
and tell Chan-sung to take him home.

848
01:13:56,190 --> 01:13:57,860
This isn't a place for you.

849
01:13:57,942 --> 01:14:00,692
You could've ended up
in a very scary place.

850
01:14:01,111 --> 01:14:03,531
But I saw a man walking in there.

851
01:14:06,450 --> 01:14:08,910
What? What did you just say?

852
01:14:09,453 --> 01:14:10,583
Who did you see?

853
01:14:10,663 --> 01:14:12,793
A man in a suit walked in.

854
01:14:13,207 --> 01:14:15,037
I was waiting to see if he was coming out,

855
01:14:15,125 --> 01:14:16,535
but he didn't.

856
01:14:17,544 --> 01:14:19,594
I think Mr. Koo went in there.

857
01:14:19,672 --> 01:14:22,512
If he did, he'll get lost in there
and never--

858
01:16:12,743 --> 01:16:14,123
Chan-sung...

859
01:16:15,913 --> 01:16:17,163
Chan-sung?

860
01:17:45,294 --> 01:17:46,424
Chan-sung!

861
01:18:01,935 --> 01:18:04,185
I was so scared you might never come back.

862
01:20:13,317 --> 01:20:14,357
Who...

863
01:20:20,699 --> 01:20:21,949
are you?

864
01:21:18,006 --> 01:21:19,506
{\an8}<i>If he had come, I was going to throw him</i>

865
01:21:19,591 --> 01:21:22,591
{\an8}into the hell that you made
and make both of you vanish.

866
01:21:22,678 --> 01:21:24,808
{\an8}<i>I can't do that anymore.</i>

867
01:21:24,888 --> 01:21:28,848
{\an8}I ended up falling in love again.
How ridiculous.

868
01:21:31,687 --> 01:21:32,897
{\an8}<i>Eat this.</i>

869
01:21:32,979 --> 01:21:35,819
{\an8}Eat it and become an evil ghost.

870
01:21:40,237 --> 01:21:41,567
<i>Just die.</i>

871
01:21:41,988 --> 01:21:43,948
<i>I told you that she will protect me.</i>

872
01:21:47,744 --> 01:21:49,834
{\an8}Subtitle translation by Wayne Ryu

873
01:22:08,894 --> 01:22:09,944
Stop.

874
01:22:13,357 --> 01:22:14,647
What are you doing?

875
01:22:15,359 --> 01:22:17,489
These are the belongings
of the executed men.

876
01:22:17,653 --> 01:22:20,363
We were told to keep what's useful
and burn the rest.

877
01:22:34,545 --> 01:22:36,545
Don't burn the belongings of the dead.

878
01:22:38,173 --> 01:22:39,433
Gather all of them.

879
01:23:06,243 --> 01:23:08,203
Give these to the men who survived

880
01:23:08,287 --> 01:23:10,577
so that they can hold a proper funeral.

881
01:23:13,334 --> 01:23:14,344
Wait.

882
01:23:28,223 --> 01:23:29,683
I will kill you.

883
01:23:31,268 --> 01:23:33,018
I will kill you

884
01:23:34,438 --> 01:23:35,688
at all costs.

885
01:24:58,814 --> 01:24:59,944
Chan-sung!

886
01:25:07,072 --> 01:25:09,322
I was so scared you might never come back.

887
01:25:46,528 --> 01:25:47,608
Who...

888
01:25:52,034 --> 01:25:53,084
are you?

889
01:26:01,460 --> 01:26:02,380
Mr. Koo!

890
01:26:03,253 --> 01:26:04,963
-Mr. Koo!
-Mr. Koo!

891
01:26:05,380 --> 01:26:06,760
Mr. Koo!

892
01:26:13,138 --> 01:26:14,718
Thank goodness you're okay.

893
01:26:15,265 --> 01:26:17,055
We were really worried.

894
01:26:17,434 --> 01:26:18,944
My heart dropped again.

895
01:26:29,071 --> 01:26:30,951
Ms. Jang, you must've been
really startled.

896
01:26:31,156 --> 01:26:32,366
Do you feel unwell?

897
01:26:34,785 --> 01:26:35,945
No, I'm fine.

898
01:26:41,208 --> 01:26:44,088
I'm okay. I must've startled you a lot.

899
01:26:52,553 --> 01:26:54,603
Ms. Jang must be angry.

900
01:26:54,680 --> 01:26:57,720
She's probably just embarrassed
that she ran over here all startled.

901
01:26:58,475 --> 01:27:01,595
Anyway, I'm relieved
that you managed to find your way out.

902
01:27:42,060 --> 01:27:43,150
This is...

903
01:27:44,563 --> 01:27:46,573
the end for us.

904
01:27:52,029 --> 01:27:53,449
Who is that man?

905
01:27:54,072 --> 01:27:56,162
Why do you ask? You think it might be you?

906
01:27:56,325 --> 01:27:58,155
That thought did occur to me.

907
01:27:58,243 --> 01:28:01,623
What I saw could be a memory
from my past life that I don't remember.

908
01:28:03,874 --> 01:28:07,634
Koo Chan-sung will eventually
bring him to you.

909
01:28:13,550 --> 01:28:15,050
This is absurd.

910
01:28:15,552 --> 01:28:17,642
Chan-sung can't be him.

911
01:28:34,446 --> 01:28:38,366
It seems Man-wol will get seriously swayed

912
01:28:39,076 --> 01:28:40,486
by this

913
01:28:41,453 --> 01:28:43,913
small and green light.

914
01:28:48,335 --> 01:28:49,455
You've become

915
01:28:50,212 --> 01:28:52,802
very weak because you had to come back

916
01:28:52,881 --> 01:28:54,421
from the afterlife.

917
01:28:55,425 --> 01:28:57,385
And now, you're so dim.

918
01:29:22,828 --> 01:29:24,448
This alcohol is for the living.

919
01:29:24,538 --> 01:29:26,368
You almost crossed the threshold
of the afterlife,

920
01:29:26,456 --> 01:29:28,376
so hurry up and drink something
from this world.

921
01:29:30,544 --> 01:29:31,754
Thank you.

922
01:29:37,009 --> 01:29:39,799
I'm so relieved that you didn't get lost
and found your way out.

923
01:29:39,886 --> 01:29:40,846
Yes, I heard

924
01:29:40,929 --> 01:29:44,889
that time runs at a different speed there
and that I could lose my memory.

925
01:29:44,975 --> 01:29:47,015
"A man was gone for a moment
and came back,

926
01:29:47,102 --> 01:29:48,562
and 30 years had passed."

927
01:29:48,645 --> 01:29:50,605
Such a folktale wasn't a joke.

928
01:29:50,689 --> 01:29:52,319
I heard this from the Grim Reaper.

929
01:29:52,399 --> 01:29:55,399
Someone remembered his past life
on his way back from the afterlife,

930
01:29:55,485 --> 01:29:57,695
which completely ruined his life
in the living realm.

931
01:29:57,779 --> 01:29:58,779
His past life?

932
01:29:58,905 --> 01:30:01,365
Did you see anything odd
when you were there?

933
01:30:09,833 --> 01:30:13,133
I think I remember seeing
something twinkling in the dark.

934
01:30:13,211 --> 01:30:14,051
I see.

935
01:30:14,504 --> 01:30:15,804
What was that?

936
01:30:18,216 --> 01:30:20,046
We don't know. We've never gone in there.

937
01:30:21,428 --> 01:30:24,058
You got to go in there
even before we dead ones do.

938
01:30:24,222 --> 01:30:26,852
By the way, how did you manage
to return right away?

939
01:30:26,933 --> 01:30:28,103
I heard it's not easy.

940
01:30:28,185 --> 01:30:29,935
Frankly, I have no recollection
whatsoever.

941
01:30:30,395 --> 01:30:32,395
I was out of there
when I came to my senses.

942
01:30:32,481 --> 01:30:35,281
You lost your memory.
Here, drink some more.

943
01:30:37,861 --> 01:30:38,821
Ms. Jang.

944
01:30:47,162 --> 01:30:49,412
I thought the kid got on the car
to the afterlife.

945
01:30:49,790 --> 01:30:51,710
I ended up going in there,
trying to stop that.

946
01:30:51,792 --> 01:30:55,252
Both the kid and I are fine,
so don't be mad.

947
01:31:38,296 --> 01:31:39,796
I'm really fine.

948
01:31:48,598 --> 01:31:50,598
You are just Chan-sung.

949
01:31:57,232 --> 01:31:58,402
Do you still...

950
01:32:00,068 --> 01:32:01,528
see me in your dreams?

951
01:32:05,240 --> 01:32:08,160
No, I haven't seen you in my dreams

952
01:32:09,911 --> 01:32:11,581
since the day I had a very long dream.

953
01:32:14,791 --> 01:32:16,461
Then, did you see someone else?

954
01:32:16,668 --> 01:32:17,838
I haven't told you

955
01:32:18,128 --> 01:32:20,838
because I wasn't sure whether it was
a dream or just my imagination,

956
01:32:21,506 --> 01:32:22,796
but I saw that man.

957
01:32:24,217 --> 01:32:25,717
The man named Cheong-myeong.

958
01:32:29,347 --> 01:32:30,637
He was waiting for you

959
01:32:31,266 --> 01:32:33,516
by the lake all by himself.

960
01:32:35,103 --> 01:32:38,363
He was holding an ornament
with your moon-shaped symbol

961
01:32:38,815 --> 01:32:40,525
in his hands.

962
01:32:45,322 --> 01:32:46,362
Have you

963
01:32:47,699 --> 01:32:49,409
received such a gift?

964
01:32:52,495 --> 01:32:53,535
No.

965
01:32:56,791 --> 01:32:58,751
If I wasn't looking into your past,

966
01:32:58,877 --> 01:33:00,337
what was that dream about?

967
01:33:05,717 --> 01:33:08,887
You told me before
that perhaps you were seeing

968
01:33:10,096 --> 01:33:13,056
memories from your past life
that you don't remember.

969
01:33:13,141 --> 01:33:15,231
But you said that was impossible.

970
01:33:20,273 --> 01:33:21,323
Yes.

971
01:33:22,817 --> 01:33:24,147
It's impossible.

972
01:33:26,947 --> 01:33:28,277
Are you anxious

973
01:33:28,531 --> 01:33:31,121
because of how Song-hwa and Yeon-u
ended up together?

974
01:33:31,201 --> 01:33:32,911
Are you worried he might return like that?

975
01:33:33,995 --> 01:33:35,615
I won't end up like them.

976
01:33:37,540 --> 01:33:38,630
They were...

977
01:33:39,960 --> 01:33:42,500
Fine. It happened in their past lives,

978
01:33:42,671 --> 01:33:44,171
so let's say it's possible for them.

979
01:33:44,547 --> 01:33:46,757
But for me, it happened in this lifetime.

980
01:33:58,645 --> 01:34:00,935
Seeing Yeon-u with that woman

981
01:34:02,190 --> 01:34:04,440
made me think
some crazy thoughts for a moment.

982
01:34:27,173 --> 01:34:29,513
-Dad.
-Hyeong-min! Yes, I'm here.

983
01:34:30,468 --> 01:34:32,758
He fell asleep at a bus stop.

984
01:34:32,846 --> 01:34:35,346
We brought him to the hospital
because he had a fever.

985
01:34:35,432 --> 01:34:38,182
He took some medicine,
so the fever has gone down.

986
01:34:38,935 --> 01:34:40,225
Thank you so much.

987
01:34:42,897 --> 01:34:44,567
Where have you been?

988
01:34:44,691 --> 01:34:46,611
I took the bus and went to the hotel.

989
01:34:47,944 --> 01:34:50,034
He must've had a dream when he was asleep.

990
01:34:50,739 --> 01:34:53,829
I went there to see Mom,
but they said she was not there.

991
01:34:58,288 --> 01:35:00,208
When you're a little older,

992
01:35:00,957 --> 01:35:04,207
I'll tell you where your mom is
and why she had to leave.

993
01:35:04,294 --> 01:35:06,174
I'll tell you everything, okay?

994
01:35:06,713 --> 01:35:07,713
Okay.

995
01:35:08,715 --> 01:35:09,835
I'm sorry.

996
01:35:13,845 --> 01:35:17,015
If he finds out later,
will it make him less sad?

997
01:35:17,766 --> 01:35:19,806
That he will never see her again.

998
01:35:25,273 --> 01:35:26,403
Does Yu-na know

999
01:35:26,608 --> 01:35:30,528
that you're planning to leave
with your younger sister after she dies?

1000
01:35:36,493 --> 01:35:37,453
Yu-na.

1001
01:35:39,120 --> 01:35:41,460
-There's--
-Hey, Ms. Jang will yell at you

1002
01:35:41,539 --> 01:35:43,919
if you go back now,
so let's hang out a little.

1003
01:35:44,000 --> 01:35:45,420
-Well--
-I learned

1004
01:35:45,502 --> 01:35:48,132
that you get scolded less
if you wait it out a little.

1005
01:35:48,338 --> 01:35:50,798
Wait here. I need to use the ladies' room.

1006
01:35:58,181 --> 01:35:59,771
I should tell her today.

1007
01:36:09,275 --> 01:36:11,855
Ma'am, listen to this for a moment.

1008
01:36:20,912 --> 01:36:22,962
Do you like this piano melody?

1009
01:36:23,873 --> 01:36:24,873
Well...

1010
01:36:25,166 --> 01:36:26,246
Yes.

1011
01:36:27,335 --> 01:36:28,955
My friend's sister...

1012
01:36:29,754 --> 01:36:32,804
I mean, you look a lot
like my friend's grandmother.

1013
01:36:32,882 --> 01:36:36,722
May I take a photo of you
listening to music to show my friend?

1014
01:36:37,929 --> 01:36:38,929
Sure.

1015
01:36:41,599 --> 01:36:43,139
Thank you.

1016
01:36:55,572 --> 01:36:58,532
Well... Do you remember

1017
01:36:58,616 --> 01:37:01,196
your brother's name by any chance?

1018
01:37:01,744 --> 01:37:02,834
Yes, I do.

1019
01:37:04,122 --> 01:37:10,132
My brother's name is Ji Hyeon-jung.

1020
01:37:10,211 --> 01:37:11,881
You remember him?

1021
01:37:13,173 --> 01:37:14,173
Yes.

1022
01:37:20,346 --> 01:37:22,636
Hello, can I help you?

1023
01:37:23,224 --> 01:37:24,524
Hyeon-jung.

1024
01:37:25,185 --> 01:37:26,765
Yes, Hyeon-mi.

1025
01:37:27,437 --> 01:37:29,267
Were you listening to music?

1026
01:37:30,732 --> 01:37:32,072
Let's see.

1027
01:37:32,358 --> 01:37:35,898
Sir, are you the founder of this hospital,

1028
01:37:35,987 --> 01:37:38,567
Mr. Ji Hyeon-jung?

1029
01:37:38,656 --> 01:37:43,156
Yes. You must be Mr. Kim's daughter
who was hospitalized here.

1030
01:37:43,870 --> 01:37:44,950
Hold on.

1031
01:37:45,288 --> 01:37:46,788
You're

1032
01:37:47,707 --> 01:37:49,327
her brother?

1033
01:37:50,001 --> 01:37:52,131
Yes, I am. What's the matter?

1034
01:37:52,212 --> 01:37:54,592
But her brother, Ji Hyeon-jung,

1035
01:37:54,839 --> 01:37:56,629
died many years ago.

1036
01:37:57,926 --> 01:37:58,926
What?

1037
01:38:02,430 --> 01:38:05,180
Hyeon-jung?

1038
01:38:05,600 --> 01:38:07,890
-Where are you?
-Yes, I'm here.

1039
01:38:09,020 --> 01:38:10,060
Gosh.

1040
01:38:21,908 --> 01:38:23,908
There is someone who knows

1041
01:38:25,411 --> 01:38:27,371
that Ji Hyeon-jung is dead.

1042
01:38:36,381 --> 01:38:37,881
I told you not to bother Hyeon-mi.

1043
01:38:37,966 --> 01:38:40,126
Does that man have something
to do with your death?

1044
01:38:40,635 --> 01:38:42,545
Did he steal everything you had?

1045
01:38:42,804 --> 01:38:44,264
And he's living as you now?

1046
01:38:44,347 --> 01:38:47,227
-It's none of your business.
-That's why you couldn't leave.

1047
01:38:48,226 --> 01:38:50,896
You couldn't stand him living
a good life using your name.

1048
01:38:52,814 --> 01:38:55,154
-Just leave him be.
-How could I?

1049
01:38:55,233 --> 01:38:56,653
He stole your life.

1050
01:38:56,734 --> 01:38:58,534
Who cares? I'm already dead.

1051
01:38:58,611 --> 01:39:00,491
Look at yourself living a good life.

1052
01:39:07,370 --> 01:39:08,500
Right.

1053
01:39:09,080 --> 01:39:11,710
I stole someone's life too.

1054
01:39:12,584 --> 01:39:13,964
I was being too nosy.

1055
01:39:14,043 --> 01:39:15,343
Yu-na, that's not what I meant.

1056
01:39:15,420 --> 01:39:16,710
I'll mind my own business.

1057
01:39:30,101 --> 01:39:31,941
Hey, Sanchez.
Everything's going well, right?

1058
01:39:32,020 --> 01:39:33,190
-Yes.
-Give me that!

1059
01:39:33,271 --> 01:39:34,901
-Hey!
-What's up with all the noise?

1060
01:39:35,315 --> 01:39:36,515
Is someone else home?

1061
01:39:36,691 --> 01:39:38,991
Mi-ra had Detective Park
sleep in your room last night

1062
01:39:39,068 --> 01:39:40,898
because his leg was swollen.

1063
01:39:40,987 --> 01:39:42,947
I think he's fine now,
but Mi-ra kept saying

1064
01:39:43,031 --> 01:39:45,911
he must eat well as he's injured.
So we were eating.

1065
01:39:45,992 --> 01:39:47,452
But when we were having a meal,

1066
01:39:47,535 --> 01:39:50,785
Detective Park's colleagues
came over since it's their day off.

1067
01:39:50,872 --> 01:39:52,792
And then, they said I had a nice yard,

1068
01:39:52,874 --> 01:39:54,584
so they're having the watermelon
they brought.

1069
01:39:55,960 --> 01:39:57,630
Gosh, you guys look great together.

1070
01:39:59,422 --> 01:40:01,342
It's Mi-ra who invited them, right?

1071
01:40:01,466 --> 01:40:04,216
Chan-sung, it's very safe
since they're here.

1072
01:40:04,302 --> 01:40:07,722
And thanks to the incense Man-wol gave me,
it's spiritually safe too.

1073
01:40:07,805 --> 01:40:09,675
Since the detectives are here,

1074
01:40:09,766 --> 01:40:12,016
I don't need to worry
about being in danger.

1075
01:40:12,977 --> 01:40:15,517
Sanchez, put Mi-ra on the phone.
I'll talk to her.

1076
01:40:15,688 --> 01:40:16,858
Don't.

1077
01:40:17,815 --> 01:40:21,275
I'm sure she's bringing people over
in case I get depressed if I'm all alone.

1078
01:40:21,861 --> 01:40:23,911
It's nice and noisy here.

1079
01:40:23,988 --> 01:40:26,488
Chan-sung, all I could think about is
making sure

1080
01:40:26,574 --> 01:40:28,414
that they don't ruin the grass.

1081
01:40:29,327 --> 01:40:32,287
Chan-sung, you don't need
to worry about me.

1082
01:40:32,789 --> 01:40:35,249
-This is good.
-It is, right? I bought it.

1083
01:40:35,333 --> 01:40:36,793
-No, you didn't.
-I didn't?

1084
01:40:37,210 --> 01:40:38,340
I'll eat it myself.

1085
01:40:39,128 --> 01:40:40,588
Come on, you're injured.

1086
01:40:40,672 --> 01:40:41,922
My arm is fine.

1087
01:40:43,549 --> 01:40:45,969
Should I break your arm,
so you will let me feed you?

1088
01:40:47,512 --> 01:40:48,512
Here.

1089
01:40:50,765 --> 01:40:52,385
It's good, right?

1090
01:40:55,019 --> 01:40:57,479
-You can eat it yourself now.
-It's good.

1091
01:40:58,314 --> 01:40:59,194
Isn't it sweet?

1092
01:40:59,273 --> 01:41:03,243
I thought Mi-ra and Detective Park were
always fighting like enemies.

1093
01:41:03,319 --> 01:41:05,489
Now that I see them together,
they seem fine.

1094
01:41:06,030 --> 01:41:07,410
You don't need to worry.

1095
01:41:07,490 --> 01:41:09,160
I think she'll move out soon.

1096
01:41:09,742 --> 01:41:13,122
Chan-sung, I'll go eat
some watermelon now. Bye.

1097
01:41:14,622 --> 01:41:15,752
Sanchez.

1098
01:41:16,124 --> 01:41:18,134
Eat the melon the detectives bought.

1099
01:41:18,501 --> 01:41:20,501
-Come and join us.
-It's delicious.

1100
01:41:20,586 --> 01:41:21,586
Mi-ra.

1101
01:41:22,213 --> 01:41:24,803
That melon came from my fridge.

1102
01:41:26,092 --> 01:41:27,342
Is that so?

1103
01:41:28,761 --> 01:41:30,761
-Let's eat it.
-Things happen, you know.

1104
01:41:30,847 --> 01:41:32,597
-The melon did feel cool.
-Bring the cutting board.

1105
01:41:32,682 --> 01:41:34,102
What does it matter?

1106
01:41:39,313 --> 01:41:40,273
Come in.

1107
01:41:49,699 --> 01:41:50,869
Do you remember

1108
01:41:51,159 --> 01:41:54,199
that Ms. Jang invited a woman
to our hotel a while ago?

1109
01:41:54,454 --> 01:41:56,254
This is an amazing hotel.

1110
01:41:56,664 --> 01:41:59,504
And from what I've heard,
she's your friend.

1111
01:41:59,792 --> 01:42:00,882
That's right.

1112
01:42:01,544 --> 01:42:04,594
Did she cross paths with Ms. Jang
in her past lives?

1113
01:42:08,009 --> 01:42:09,549
I'm sure their connection was ill-fated.

1114
01:42:10,595 --> 01:42:12,175
We have never

1115
01:42:12,555 --> 01:42:16,095
tried to figure out Ms. Jang's story

1116
01:42:16,684 --> 01:42:19,354
because we always assumed
that she had no intention

1117
01:42:19,437 --> 01:42:22,017
of leaving after resolving her grudges.

1118
01:42:23,399 --> 01:42:26,939
But now, the tree that tied her down here
has changed.

1119
01:42:27,028 --> 01:42:29,818
And I think the changes have been brought

1120
01:42:29,906 --> 01:42:33,366
by you and the connections
you have brought.

1121
01:42:33,743 --> 01:42:35,123
Your assumption...

1122
01:42:37,038 --> 01:42:38,118
is correct.

1123
01:42:39,749 --> 01:42:41,249
Will Ms. Jang face

1124
01:42:41,834 --> 01:42:44,174
more connections from her past,
not just that lady?

1125
01:42:45,922 --> 01:42:47,092
He's already here.

1126
01:42:47,882 --> 01:42:48,972
And I'm sure

1127
01:42:49,842 --> 01:42:51,052
more will come shortly.

1128
01:42:54,013 --> 01:42:57,643
I'll probably end up bringing
the man to Ms. Jang like the others.

1129
01:42:58,601 --> 01:43:02,271
That must be why Mago brought you
to our hotel.

1130
01:43:02,480 --> 01:43:04,190
Then, you must have crossed paths

1131
01:43:04,273 --> 01:43:06,443
with Ms. Jang in your past life as well.

1132
01:43:07,026 --> 01:43:08,146
No, I have not.

1133
01:43:08,569 --> 01:43:09,609
Is that so?

1134
01:43:10,321 --> 01:43:11,531
That's odd.

1135
01:43:11,823 --> 01:43:14,033
If you have never met her
in your past life,

1136
01:43:14,116 --> 01:43:17,246
why did Mago choose you of all people?

1137
01:43:23,459 --> 01:43:25,959
I'm sure the deity must have
a reason for bringing you to her.

1138
01:43:26,295 --> 01:43:29,295
Anyway, it resulted in love.

1139
01:43:31,008 --> 01:43:32,178
I will continue

1140
01:43:33,761 --> 01:43:35,181
to stay with her.

1141
01:43:39,392 --> 01:43:41,522
My heart breaks for Ms. Jang.

1142
01:43:42,144 --> 01:43:43,234
Soon,

1143
01:43:44,313 --> 01:43:46,653
she will have to face someone

1144
01:43:48,109 --> 01:43:50,109
who pains her the most.

1145
01:44:08,045 --> 01:44:09,625
Man-wol.

1146
01:44:10,673 --> 01:44:12,303
Why are you leaving?

1147
01:44:12,383 --> 01:44:13,803
I don't want to see you.

1148
01:44:15,386 --> 01:44:18,256
Just admire the flowers you like so much
as much as you want,

1149
01:44:18,931 --> 01:44:19,891
and leave.

1150
01:44:19,974 --> 01:44:21,024
Then,

1151
01:44:21,475 --> 01:44:24,055
will you let him just pass by,

1152
01:44:24,645 --> 01:44:25,935
pretending to be clueless?

1153
01:44:30,568 --> 01:44:32,698
You have met him.

1154
01:44:40,661 --> 01:44:42,541
You can't run away from it.

1155
01:44:43,289 --> 01:44:44,749
He's already

1156
01:44:45,499 --> 01:44:46,999
by your side.

1157
01:44:54,258 --> 01:44:56,678
I finally get to give this to you.

1158
01:44:59,764 --> 01:45:00,934
It's yours.

1159
01:45:18,949 --> 01:45:20,159
But I saw that man.

1160
01:45:20,910 --> 01:45:22,330
The man named Cheong-myeong.

1161
01:45:24,080 --> 01:45:27,580
He was holding an ornament
with your moon-shaped symbol

1162
01:45:28,292 --> 01:45:30,092
in his hands.

1163
01:45:34,298 --> 01:45:35,838
Is it Chan-sung?

1164
01:45:37,176 --> 01:45:38,586
If it is him,

1165
01:45:39,845 --> 01:45:41,715
will you be able to accept it?

1166
01:45:45,393 --> 01:45:46,773
Is Chan-sung

1167
01:45:47,603 --> 01:45:49,113
that man?

1168
01:45:52,233 --> 01:45:55,113
The man you've been waiting
for over 1,000 years has finally shown up,

1169
01:45:55,194 --> 01:45:56,654
but you don't seem happy.

1170
01:45:59,615 --> 01:46:03,235
You were sure
that once he came to you in this world,

1171
01:46:03,786 --> 01:46:06,366
you'd kill him and vanish yourself.

1172
01:46:07,748 --> 01:46:10,038
Are you second-guessing yourself now?

1173
01:46:14,630 --> 01:46:15,840
So I asked...

1174
01:46:17,967 --> 01:46:19,717
if that man is Chan-sung.

1175
01:46:20,010 --> 01:46:23,850
You have fed the hatred of yours
for a long time.

1176
01:46:24,515 --> 01:46:28,055
Why don't you let go of your hatred
with your love that took ages

1177
01:46:29,103 --> 01:46:30,563
to reach you?

1178
01:46:36,694 --> 01:46:39,744
I have hated the man for over 1,000 years.

1179
01:46:41,741 --> 01:46:45,121
But you make me see him
as a man I fell in love with?

1180
01:46:47,204 --> 01:46:49,874
I'm curious to find out which man

1181
01:46:50,541 --> 01:46:52,331
you'll see him as.

1182
01:46:53,419 --> 01:46:57,049
Will you see him as Go Cheong-myeong
and vanish yourself?

1183
01:46:57,798 --> 01:47:00,838
Or will you see him as Koo Chan-sung
and be saved?

1184
01:47:01,927 --> 01:47:03,137
That is...

1185
01:47:04,430 --> 01:47:06,140
up to you.

1186
01:48:03,155 --> 01:48:04,275
Jang Man-wol.

1187
01:48:10,371 --> 01:48:13,121
Every sight you see with me
will look different.

1188
01:48:13,207 --> 01:48:15,787
The view is much better
now that I'm with you.

1189
01:48:18,712 --> 01:48:20,172
I'm proud of you,

1190
01:48:20,673 --> 01:48:21,883
Man-wol.

1191
01:49:17,146 --> 01:49:18,356
I told you

1192
01:49:19,648 --> 01:49:21,358
to trust me.

1193
01:49:46,550 --> 01:49:47,930
Chan-sung.

1194
01:50:31,220 --> 01:50:32,300
Ms. Jang.

1195
01:50:36,767 --> 01:50:38,977
Are you all right?

1196
01:50:40,062 --> 01:50:42,022
You look very pale.

1197
01:50:53,784 --> 01:50:55,204
A moment ago,

1198
01:50:56,662 --> 01:50:59,672
I killed Chan-sung in my thoughts.

1199
01:51:04,295 --> 01:51:05,835
He could be...

1200
01:51:07,715 --> 01:51:11,005
the reincarnation of the man
I hate the most.

1201
01:51:11,677 --> 01:51:12,927
I'm sure it isn't him.

1202
01:51:14,013 --> 01:51:16,393
Mr. Koo also said it wasn't him.

1203
01:51:17,558 --> 01:51:18,638
Right.

1204
01:51:19,393 --> 01:51:21,023
It might not be him.

1205
01:51:21,520 --> 01:51:24,770
But as long as there's the slightest
possibility that it could be him,

1206
01:51:25,149 --> 01:51:27,149
I will never be able

1207
01:51:28,360 --> 01:51:30,280
to see Chan-sung properly.

1208
01:51:31,488 --> 01:51:32,568
Now

1209
01:51:33,282 --> 01:51:34,912
what will you do?

1210
01:51:48,672 --> 01:51:51,512
I can never kill Chan-sung.

1211
01:51:55,888 --> 01:51:58,718
Mago says I have to empty out everything.

1212
01:52:02,061 --> 01:52:03,981
Now I have to think hard...

1213
01:52:06,690 --> 01:52:08,690
about how to do that.

1214
01:52:39,723 --> 01:52:41,643
I bought them at the shop you like.

1215
01:52:41,850 --> 01:52:44,520
You will feel better
if you eat something sweet.

1216
01:52:46,271 --> 01:52:47,481
Come and sit down.

1217
01:52:53,904 --> 01:52:55,324
What do you have in your hand?

1218
01:53:04,081 --> 01:53:07,291
It's the ornament I saw in my dreams.

1219
01:53:10,838 --> 01:53:12,758
I guess this came from your dream.

1220
01:53:14,299 --> 01:53:15,879
Mago gave it to me.

1221
01:53:16,051 --> 01:53:18,931
In my dreams,
it didn't have any blood on it.

1222
01:53:19,054 --> 01:53:21,064
I told you he died on my sword.

1223
01:53:22,391 --> 01:53:23,641
This blood

1224
01:53:24,226 --> 01:53:26,726
must be filled with the hatred of me.

1225
01:53:26,937 --> 01:53:29,107
Why did Mago give you
such an ominous thing?

1226
01:53:29,773 --> 01:53:31,573
Give it to me. I'll keep it for you.

1227
01:53:36,738 --> 01:53:38,368
I'll get rid of this myself.

1228
01:53:39,283 --> 01:53:41,083
The moon covered in blood

1229
01:53:41,702 --> 01:53:42,952
must be destroyed.

1230
01:53:43,871 --> 01:53:45,751
Mago always tells me

1231
01:53:46,206 --> 01:53:48,036
to empty the moon

1232
01:53:48,959 --> 01:53:50,289
that is filled with hatred.

1233
01:53:51,211 --> 01:53:52,631
Can you do that?

1234
01:53:55,174 --> 01:53:56,384
I have to.

1235
01:53:59,136 --> 01:54:00,886
I want to call in

1236
01:54:02,723 --> 01:54:04,143
the moon covered in blood.

1237
01:54:09,813 --> 01:54:12,573
Mr. Koo.

1238
01:54:13,233 --> 01:54:14,573
You were here.

1239
01:54:17,821 --> 01:54:19,451
The Grim Reaper is looking for you.

1240
01:54:21,450 --> 01:54:22,330
Go on.

1241
01:54:34,463 --> 01:54:36,883
I have found the vengeful ghost
that cursed you.

1242
01:54:37,174 --> 01:54:38,684
You've found Seol Ji-won.

1243
01:54:38,926 --> 01:54:41,926
Has he become more powerful as he wanted?

1244
01:54:42,221 --> 01:54:44,971
Do you think a vengeful ghost
that holds unjustifiable resentment

1245
01:54:45,182 --> 01:54:47,352
can become powerful as he wishes?

1246
01:54:47,976 --> 01:54:51,936
He is only hiding in the dark
like a gutter rat.

1247
01:54:52,147 --> 01:54:53,147
It's good to know

1248
01:54:53,232 --> 01:54:56,532
that he hasn't become
as stronger as his evil mind.

1249
01:54:56,860 --> 01:54:59,910
He's just hiding in the dark
like a coward.

1250
01:55:02,533 --> 01:55:04,083
Can you help me?

1251
01:55:05,369 --> 01:55:07,409
I heard you were good at acting as bait.

1252
01:55:08,080 --> 01:55:10,370
I won't reveal who recommended you.

1253
01:55:10,582 --> 01:55:11,922
I'm sure it's Mr. Kim.

1254
01:55:14,962 --> 01:55:18,632
I'll take it that one of my colleagues
thinks highly of my skills.

1255
01:55:19,132 --> 01:55:22,512
Many human managers worked here.

1256
01:55:23,303 --> 01:55:24,643
Among them, you are...

1257
01:55:28,308 --> 01:55:29,848
This is my assessment.

1258
01:55:32,729 --> 01:55:33,729
Thank you.

1259
01:55:36,608 --> 01:55:40,448
Were you there when the Guest House
of the Moon first opened?

1260
01:55:41,280 --> 01:55:42,280
Yes.

1261
01:55:42,990 --> 01:55:44,870
I guided a number of souls

1262
01:55:44,950 --> 01:55:47,410
from this place to the other world.

1263
01:55:48,912 --> 01:55:51,332
Take good care of your guests.

1264
01:55:51,582 --> 01:55:52,582
Especially,

1265
01:55:53,292 --> 01:55:54,592
your first guest.

1266
01:55:57,087 --> 01:55:58,917
Who was the first guest of this place?

1267
01:56:00,966 --> 01:56:04,136
Mago said that the first guest was
the most important.

1268
01:56:04,886 --> 01:56:06,676
I have not yet guided...

1269
01:56:08,682 --> 01:56:10,482
the first guest of this place.

1270
01:56:12,561 --> 01:56:13,901
Nobody in this place

1271
01:56:14,813 --> 01:56:18,033
has seen the faint light of his existence.

1272
01:56:18,775 --> 01:56:20,685
How is that possible?

1273
01:56:20,819 --> 01:56:22,859
I do not give answers.

1274
01:56:23,780 --> 01:56:25,240
I only guide them to the end.

1275
01:56:26,366 --> 01:56:27,326
For now,

1276
01:56:29,870 --> 01:56:31,460
let's go catch that vengeful ghost.

1277
01:57:03,820 --> 01:57:05,780
Since it has the moon-shaped symbol,

1278
01:57:06,865 --> 01:57:09,485
he must have made it for you.

1279
01:57:11,912 --> 01:57:15,542
And you would've been so happy
if you received it.

1280
01:57:19,169 --> 01:57:21,879
That's the most
disgusting thing about you.

1281
01:57:37,771 --> 01:57:39,061
If he would come,

1282
01:57:40,982 --> 01:57:43,112
I was going to throw him
into the hell that you made

1283
01:57:43,652 --> 01:57:45,702
and make both of you vanish.

1284
01:57:51,159 --> 01:57:52,989
But because of the scheming
of the deities,

1285
01:57:53,495 --> 01:57:55,535
I can't do that anymore.

1286
01:57:57,874 --> 01:57:58,924
I...

1287
01:58:00,752 --> 01:58:03,422
ended up falling in love again.
How ridiculous.

1288
01:58:08,385 --> 01:58:10,175
Leaning on that love,

1289
01:58:13,598 --> 01:58:16,138
I tried to ignore you.

1290
01:58:17,936 --> 01:58:19,516
But you just had to

1291
01:58:20,105 --> 01:58:22,515
drag me down again.

1292
01:58:32,534 --> 01:58:33,704
I will

1293
01:58:34,703 --> 01:58:36,203
put you in here

1294
01:58:37,497 --> 01:58:40,497
and dump it in a trash bin around here.

1295
01:58:41,960 --> 01:58:43,800
You will go berserk.

1296
01:58:47,466 --> 01:58:49,966
And we will vanish together.

1297
01:59:41,686 --> 01:59:42,766
Seol Ji-won.

1298
01:59:43,271 --> 01:59:44,271
Come out.

1299
01:59:47,484 --> 01:59:49,114
I know you're hiding in here.

1300
01:59:50,278 --> 01:59:52,738
The Grim Reaper is on his way to take you.

1301
02:00:04,084 --> 02:00:05,254
There you are.

1302
02:00:08,213 --> 02:00:11,683
So you went from being a smug jerk
to a loser.

1303
02:00:16,638 --> 02:00:18,388
I have something for you.

1304
02:00:24,980 --> 02:00:26,480
Eat this.

1305
02:00:28,775 --> 02:00:29,985
Eat it...

1306
02:00:32,320 --> 02:00:33,820
and become an evil ghost.

1307
02:00:56,720 --> 02:01:00,060
So he ended up hiding in a place
he was familiar with.

1308
02:01:00,223 --> 02:01:03,313
He's in the darkness, but he will reveal
himself once he sees you.

1309
02:01:19,034 --> 02:01:21,544
Jang Man-wol, you're here too?

1310
02:01:23,288 --> 02:01:24,578
Yes, I came earlier.

1311
02:01:26,333 --> 02:01:27,503
Did you catch him?

1312
02:01:30,045 --> 02:01:31,205
I let him go.

1313
02:01:34,716 --> 02:01:36,676
You'll be in danger soon

1314
02:01:37,594 --> 02:01:38,894
because I gave him

1315
02:01:40,513 --> 02:01:42,433
a very special gift.

1316
02:01:45,602 --> 02:01:48,982
And you'll have to take him
more seriously than before.

1317
02:01:50,190 --> 02:01:53,610
He might go crazy
with his new-found powers.

1318
02:01:55,236 --> 02:01:56,696
What are you doing?

1319
02:01:58,073 --> 02:01:59,283
Chan-sung.

1320
02:02:01,952 --> 02:02:04,162
Mago said that you're him.

1321
02:02:15,340 --> 02:02:17,380
I need to kill you,

1322
02:02:18,426 --> 02:02:20,136
but I won't be able to.

1323
02:02:22,931 --> 02:02:25,021
I just like you too much.

1324
02:02:31,731 --> 02:02:33,781
I won't protect you though.

1325
02:02:35,068 --> 02:02:37,898
I've waited
for over 1,000 years to kill you.

1326
02:02:38,321 --> 02:02:39,991
So if I protect you now,

1327
02:02:41,032 --> 02:02:43,032
I'll be making a mockery of my grudges.

1328
02:02:50,542 --> 02:02:52,382
If he becomes an evil ghost,

1329
02:02:52,627 --> 02:02:55,257
you'll vanish
because you helped him become stronger.

1330
02:03:00,135 --> 02:03:01,385
Whatever.

1331
02:03:06,266 --> 02:03:08,686
You're a human adored by Mago,

1332
02:03:09,310 --> 02:03:11,480
so they'll interfere
before the evil ghost gets to you.

1333
02:03:12,564 --> 02:03:13,734
And...

1334
02:03:15,483 --> 02:03:17,193
you'll vanish.

1335
02:03:23,783 --> 02:03:26,243
So I ended up using you.

1336
02:03:29,289 --> 02:03:31,789
It's pathetic I called it love.

1337
02:03:51,519 --> 02:03:54,269
Jang Man-wol!

1338
02:04:10,413 --> 02:04:11,463
What's with the hotel?

1339
02:04:11,539 --> 02:04:12,539
I don't know.

1340
02:04:12,624 --> 02:04:15,424
All the lights in the building
have gone out.

1341
02:04:28,056 --> 02:04:31,266
Mr. Koo, what happened to Ms. Jang?

1342
02:04:31,476 --> 02:04:33,056
I think there was a misunderstanding.

1343
02:04:33,144 --> 02:04:34,814
Do you know where she is?

1344
02:04:34,896 --> 02:04:37,106
She went into the garden
where the Moon Tree stands

1345
02:04:37,190 --> 02:04:38,650
and barricaded the door.

1346
02:04:39,692 --> 02:04:41,242
No one can enter.

1347
02:05:09,222 --> 02:05:12,182
We should check on our guests first.

1348
02:05:12,267 --> 02:05:14,557
I don't understand
why we're in trouble now.

1349
02:05:28,700 --> 02:05:29,910
Ms. Jang,

1350
02:05:30,285 --> 02:05:32,825
what on earth are you up to?

1351
02:05:37,333 --> 02:05:38,503
Is it true?

1352
02:05:39,460 --> 02:05:41,590
Am I truly that man from her past

1353
02:05:42,714 --> 02:05:44,384
who Ms. Jang loathes?

1354
02:05:45,300 --> 02:05:48,010
I doubt that's what she said

1355
02:05:48,344 --> 02:05:49,474
since he is

1356
02:05:50,471 --> 02:05:51,891
right here.

1357
02:06:11,618 --> 02:06:13,908
You've met him before, you know.

1358
02:06:32,138 --> 02:06:33,308
How...

1359
02:06:34,682 --> 02:06:35,982
is this him?

1360
02:06:37,143 --> 02:06:38,393
He is

1361
02:06:39,938 --> 02:06:42,018
the first guest who stayed

1362
02:06:42,774 --> 02:06:44,614
at Man-wol's Guest House of the Moon.

1363
02:06:54,285 --> 02:06:55,825
I should take him to her.

1364
02:06:55,912 --> 02:06:56,832
Actually,

1365
02:06:58,414 --> 02:07:01,084
shouldn't you stop her
from vanishing first?

1366
02:07:02,502 --> 02:07:06,382
Find the thing Man-wol handed over
to the evil ghost.

1367
02:07:07,131 --> 02:07:08,841
Once the evil ghost makes his move,

1368
02:07:09,425 --> 02:07:11,545
it will be irreversible.

1369
02:07:18,101 --> 02:07:20,941
Since we got the overtime pay,

1370
02:07:21,020 --> 02:07:22,310
let's grab a drink.

1371
02:07:22,397 --> 02:07:24,107
-Sure.
-Let's go.

1372
02:07:31,489 --> 02:07:33,989
I hear he cursed his wife,
wishing her dead.

1373
02:07:34,158 --> 02:07:36,658
What a piece of garbage.

1374
02:07:36,744 --> 02:07:38,254
Does he have no shame?

1375
02:08:34,218 --> 02:08:36,008
Who are you?

1376
02:08:36,095 --> 02:08:38,175
You should get out of here. Hurry.

1377
02:08:43,352 --> 02:08:44,852
Hi, my friend.

1378
02:08:51,152 --> 02:08:53,202
I was going to visit you
after I had some fun.

1379
02:08:53,279 --> 02:08:54,609
But I guess you were in a hurry.

1380
02:08:54,781 --> 02:08:55,991
How did you find me?

1381
02:08:56,074 --> 02:08:59,494
I found you thanks to the owner
of the thing you recently picked up.

1382
02:09:02,121 --> 02:09:03,161
This?

1383
02:09:03,289 --> 02:09:05,709
I came to take that back. Give it to me.

1384
02:09:06,209 --> 02:09:07,669
How are you going to do that?

1385
02:09:09,003 --> 02:09:10,763
You'll die before you can take it from me.

1386
02:09:22,725 --> 02:09:24,095
So this is

1387
02:09:25,103 --> 02:09:26,983
how you've come to face me.

1388
02:09:59,345 --> 02:10:00,845
I guess you're not going to give up.

1389
02:10:01,097 --> 02:10:02,467
Let's see how long you'll last.

1390
02:10:03,933 --> 02:10:05,563
I was just buying time.

1391
02:10:06,435 --> 02:10:07,765
The time has come.

1392
02:10:08,813 --> 02:10:10,153
The moon's showing itself.

1393
02:10:17,905 --> 02:10:19,945
Why do you think she gave that to you?

1394
02:10:20,158 --> 02:10:21,948
I told you that she will protect me.

1395
02:10:24,912 --> 02:10:26,372
You see that moon-shaped symbol?

1396
02:10:29,041 --> 02:10:30,421
Once the moon fully reveals itself,

1397
02:10:30,626 --> 02:10:32,496
you'll be doomed for having that with you.

1398
02:10:32,587 --> 02:10:33,877
Don't try to fool me.

1399
02:10:33,963 --> 02:10:35,883
I told you
that death isn't the end, didn't I?

1400
02:10:36,465 --> 02:10:39,215
I tried to stop you,
but you just chose to die.

1401
02:10:42,847 --> 02:10:45,847
Now, what awaits you is horrendous hell.

1402
02:10:46,767 --> 02:10:48,227
Goodbye, Seol Ji-won.

1403
02:11:07,997 --> 02:11:09,327
How dare you lie to me?

1404
02:11:09,832 --> 02:11:11,172
Just die.

1405
02:11:18,591 --> 02:11:20,091
I never lied to you.

1406
02:11:23,012 --> 02:11:24,562
You're really doomed.

1407
02:12:00,925 --> 02:12:04,345
I was also once
a vengeful ghost full of spite.

1408
02:12:04,428 --> 02:12:07,138
We've been dead for 770 years in total.

1409
02:12:07,223 --> 02:12:09,683
But you're nothing but a runt
that just died.

1410
02:12:09,767 --> 02:12:11,687
How dare you act up this way?

1411
02:12:16,524 --> 02:12:18,994
Take what you found,
and go back to the hotel.

1412
02:12:20,569 --> 02:12:21,609
Okay.

1413
02:12:43,968 --> 02:12:45,298
I caught him.

1414
02:12:45,469 --> 02:12:48,639
We did all the work.
You're just taking credit for it.

1415
02:12:59,567 --> 02:13:02,947
You gave yourself to the vengeful ghost
and tried to turn him into an evil one.

1416
02:13:03,696 --> 02:13:06,156
I cannot forgive you for that.

1417
02:13:07,158 --> 02:13:10,578
I took out the most horrid hell
that I had deep down inside me

1418
02:13:12,455 --> 02:13:14,455
and gave it to the evil spirit.

1419
02:13:14,915 --> 02:13:17,165
Then what does that make you now?

1420
02:13:19,045 --> 02:13:21,205
Are you just a heartbroken moon

1421
02:13:21,422 --> 02:13:25,262
that blooms and withers flowers

1422
02:13:25,760 --> 02:13:28,050
as time repeats itself?

1423
02:13:34,226 --> 02:13:35,896
Just make me vanish.

1424
02:13:53,037 --> 02:13:53,947
No!

1425
02:13:58,793 --> 02:13:59,753
I brought it back.

1426
02:14:00,795 --> 02:14:02,505
There's no reason she must vanish now.

1427
02:14:02,713 --> 02:14:03,553
Please leave.

1428
02:14:05,049 --> 02:14:06,629
Just make me vanish!

1429
02:14:14,266 --> 02:14:15,266
Fine.

1430
02:14:16,310 --> 02:14:17,730
Go ahead and have what you want.

1431
02:14:20,815 --> 02:14:22,565
If you must torment yourself like that,

1432
02:14:23,150 --> 02:14:25,530
I'll become the guy you hate so much.

1433
02:14:30,574 --> 02:14:31,744
Kill me.

1434
02:14:47,466 --> 02:14:50,216
I promised I'd stay by your side
even if I have to die

1435
02:14:52,096 --> 02:14:54,056
for getting in your way.

1436
02:15:50,362 --> 02:15:52,362
The man you've been waiting for...

1437
02:15:55,201 --> 02:15:56,741
is actually here.

1438
02:16:02,208 --> 02:16:03,668
You came all the way here.

1439
02:16:03,918 --> 02:16:06,168
So you should listen to
what happened to the moon...

1440
02:16:08,839 --> 02:16:09,799
covered in blood.

1441
02:16:12,301 --> 02:16:14,681
That way, you'll be able
to empty your grudges.

1442
02:16:25,397 --> 02:16:27,897
Is this the afterlife?

1443
02:16:28,609 --> 02:16:32,989
The afterlife that you'll encounter
won't be so magnificent.

1444
02:16:33,697 --> 02:16:36,737
But there are some people
who wish to see you before you leave.

1445
02:16:37,535 --> 02:16:38,575
Me?

1446
02:16:38,786 --> 02:16:41,286
Our hotel guests are waiting for you.

1447
02:16:43,290 --> 02:16:46,210
This is a special service for them.

1448
02:16:48,295 --> 02:16:50,085
This number is such a cliché.

1449
02:16:51,215 --> 02:16:53,545
What is this? Is it the hell?

1450
02:16:53,968 --> 02:16:55,798
You'll find out once you go inside.

1451
02:17:35,426 --> 02:17:37,796
Do you remember what you said to all of us

1452
02:17:37,886 --> 02:17:39,846
right before you killed us?

1453
02:17:44,602 --> 02:17:45,732
Seol Ji-won.

1454
02:18:03,829 --> 02:18:06,459
We should soundproof the hotel rooms.

1455
02:18:25,351 --> 02:18:28,731
YOU'RE INVITED TO HOTEL DEL LUNA

1456
02:18:48,874 --> 02:18:53,254
JANG MAN-WOL

1457
02:18:59,426 --> 02:19:02,136
YOU'RE INVITED TO HOTEL DEL LUNA
PRESIDENT JANG MAN-WOL

1458
02:19:06,392 --> 02:19:07,982
"Hotel del Luna"?

1459
02:19:08,727 --> 02:19:10,397
Mr. Koo Chan-sung works here?

1460
02:19:10,479 --> 02:19:13,689
Yes, the owner of the hotel invited you.

1461
02:19:15,067 --> 02:19:17,897
She invited the doctor too.
You two should come together.

1462
02:19:25,119 --> 02:19:27,199
DEAR MR. PARK YEONG-SU

1463
02:19:27,705 --> 02:19:28,955
Jang Man-wol?

1464
02:19:29,957 --> 02:19:30,787
DEAR MS. LEE MI-RA

1465
02:19:30,874 --> 02:19:31,964
What's that?

1466
02:19:32,376 --> 02:19:33,916
An invitation to a hotel.

1467
02:19:34,003 --> 02:19:36,213
I've already been there once
as my friend works there.

1468
02:19:36,296 --> 02:19:37,296
It's such a nice hotel.

1469
02:19:37,381 --> 02:19:38,511
Where is it?

1470
02:19:38,590 --> 02:19:40,130
Not everyone can go.

1471
02:19:40,759 --> 02:19:44,469
You can't go there without an invitation.
It's a special hotel.

1472
02:19:45,305 --> 02:19:46,345
Very special.

1473
02:19:56,984 --> 02:19:58,154
Welcome.

1474
02:19:59,820 --> 02:20:02,570
I'll take you to our Sky Lounge,
the pride of our hotel.

1475
02:20:05,075 --> 02:20:06,865
Wow.

1476
02:20:08,162 --> 02:20:10,042
You came to this fancy place
all by yourself?

1477
02:20:10,622 --> 02:20:13,792
Welcome.
We have a table ready for you inside.

1478
02:20:13,876 --> 02:20:14,956
This way, please.

1479
02:20:16,295 --> 02:20:20,165
Here, everyone gets drunk
and has a dream about their past lives.

1480
02:20:20,257 --> 02:20:22,177
And I'm the bartender here.

1481
02:20:22,259 --> 02:20:24,889
Today, the deities made an exception
for the two of you

1482
02:20:24,970 --> 02:20:28,560
and gave me permission
to let you have a taste

1483
02:20:28,640 --> 02:20:30,230
of one of your past lives.

1484
02:20:30,601 --> 02:20:31,481
The deities?

1485
02:20:31,560 --> 02:20:34,610
He means he'll impress us
with super delicious drinks.

1486
02:20:35,064 --> 02:20:37,364
I blacked out last time,
so I don't remember much.

1487
02:20:37,441 --> 02:20:39,491
This time, I should drink slowly.

1488
02:20:39,818 --> 02:20:40,818
Give us our drinks.

1489
02:20:53,916 --> 02:20:55,786
This is a petal.

1490
02:20:55,876 --> 02:20:58,336
It's a petal from the Moon Tree.

1491
02:20:58,420 --> 02:20:59,710
The Moon Tree?

1492
02:20:59,797 --> 02:21:02,257
There is such a tree?

1493
02:21:02,341 --> 02:21:04,221
I'm sure there is.

1494
02:21:05,719 --> 02:21:06,929
This is so pretty.

1495
02:21:09,973 --> 02:21:13,023
They're here in this hotel now.

1496
02:21:15,229 --> 02:21:16,649
You'll be able to find out...

1497
02:21:18,107 --> 02:21:20,187
more about him through them.

1498
02:22:04,570 --> 02:22:05,610
Cheong-myeong.

1499
02:22:18,709 --> 02:22:20,709
My father is looking for you.

1500
02:22:21,545 --> 02:22:23,335
Why is he looking for me?

1501
02:22:23,422 --> 02:22:27,932
We received a tip that you are in league
with the rebels from Dongmo Mountain.

1502
02:22:32,931 --> 02:22:35,181
You will die if you go see my father now.

1503
02:22:35,475 --> 02:22:37,435
So I sent some soldiers

1504
02:22:38,896 --> 02:22:41,726
to capture everyone in that woman's gang.

1505
02:22:42,524 --> 02:22:44,364
What do you mean?

1506
02:22:44,443 --> 02:22:46,743
Those bandits are
the remnants of Goguryeo.

1507
02:22:46,820 --> 02:22:49,030
If you capture all of them
and take them to my father,

1508
02:22:49,114 --> 02:22:50,624
he will no longer suspect you.

1509
02:22:51,992 --> 02:22:55,452
They're just wandering thieves
that steal from peddlers.

1510
02:22:55,537 --> 02:22:57,367
If you are executed as a traitor,

1511
02:22:57,623 --> 02:22:59,333
all your subordinates

1512
02:22:59,625 --> 02:23:02,705
as well as everyone
who is related to you will die.

1513
02:23:04,129 --> 02:23:05,879
Even if there are hundreds of people,

1514
02:23:06,256 --> 02:23:08,756
my father will kill them all
as he is afraid of a coup.

1515
02:23:12,095 --> 02:23:13,965
Go and capture them all.

1516
02:24:18,870 --> 02:24:21,040
Why are you taking the innocent villagers?

1517
02:24:21,123 --> 02:24:23,043
You should just capture us thieves.

1518
02:24:23,125 --> 02:24:25,165
I'm not here to catch you thieves.

1519
02:24:25,585 --> 02:24:27,245
I came to quell the rebels.

1520
02:24:27,754 --> 02:24:28,764
What?

1521
02:24:28,922 --> 02:24:31,632
I'll try to save them even if that means
they must become slaves.

1522
02:24:32,134 --> 02:24:33,264
But for me to do that,

1523
02:24:33,343 --> 02:24:35,803
all of you thieves must be killed
as rebels.

1524
02:24:36,221 --> 02:24:37,511
Why...

1525
02:24:38,390 --> 02:24:39,770
Why are you doing this?

1526
02:24:43,061 --> 02:24:45,611
I wanted to find a way
to join hands with you.

1527
02:24:47,274 --> 02:24:50,654
I wished to go to the new country
in Dongmo Mountain

1528
02:24:51,987 --> 02:24:53,447
with you.

1529
02:24:56,950 --> 02:24:58,450
But I got busted.

1530
02:24:58,535 --> 02:25:00,655
And now, I must take your lives

1531
02:25:01,830 --> 02:25:02,910
to cover it up.

1532
02:25:03,999 --> 02:25:05,669
After I bury all of it,

1533
02:25:06,710 --> 02:25:09,460
I will pay for what I did
with my own life.

1534
02:25:09,880 --> 02:25:11,760
No, don't.

1535
02:25:17,220 --> 02:25:18,640
Just save Man-wol.

1536
02:25:19,473 --> 02:25:20,773
And to do that,

1537
02:25:20,849 --> 02:25:23,849
you must live as a traitor
instead of telling her all the excuses

1538
02:25:24,770 --> 02:25:26,480
that you told me.

1539
02:25:30,484 --> 02:25:32,194
Then Man-wol will live.

1540
02:25:45,082 --> 02:25:47,632
He made a promise to Yeon-u.

1541
02:25:59,596 --> 02:26:02,466
He's always been here.

1542
02:26:09,398 --> 02:26:15,528
He was the first guest
of the Guest House of the Moon.

1543
02:26:19,116 --> 02:26:23,786
You're not the only one
who's been paying for the past sins here

1544
02:26:24,955 --> 02:26:26,575
all these years.

1545
02:27:10,792 --> 02:27:12,712
Thanks to you,
I made a great contribution.

1546
02:27:20,635 --> 02:27:22,095
I will kill you.

1547
02:27:23,430 --> 02:27:25,310
I will kill you...

1548
02:27:26,766 --> 02:27:28,266
at all costs.

1549
02:27:31,271 --> 02:27:32,811
If you wish to kill me,

1550
02:27:35,317 --> 02:27:37,237
you will have to stay alive.

1551
02:28:44,344 --> 02:28:46,014
You must live as a traitor.

1552
02:28:46,930 --> 02:28:48,810
Then Man-wol will live.

1553
02:29:17,836 --> 02:29:19,336
I've been waiting for you.

1554
02:29:20,589 --> 02:29:24,429
I hope there won't be any hesitation
when you swing your sword at me.

1555
02:29:25,927 --> 02:29:27,217
If so,

1556
02:29:28,305 --> 02:29:30,095
I won't hesitate

1557
02:29:31,433 --> 02:29:33,443
to throw myself at the sword.

1558
02:30:06,968 --> 02:30:08,548
You have never

1559
02:30:09,763 --> 02:30:13,683
uttered his name. Not even once.

1560
02:30:20,815 --> 02:30:22,355
If you call his name,

1561
02:30:23,318 --> 02:30:25,238
he will show himself.

1562
02:30:30,700 --> 02:30:32,990
Have you been here the whole time?

1563
02:30:38,875 --> 02:30:41,245
If so, show yourself to me.

1564
02:30:44,631 --> 02:30:46,131
Go Cheong-myeong.

1565
02:31:56,578 --> 02:31:58,828
Tell me if there's anything else
you wish to tell me.

1566
02:32:00,790 --> 02:32:02,210
I'll listen to it.

1567
02:32:04,753 --> 02:32:07,013
There's no more excuse to tell you.

1568
02:32:09,424 --> 02:32:10,554
Man-wol.

1569
02:32:14,053 --> 02:32:16,013
You told me in your last moment

1570
02:32:17,432 --> 02:32:19,522
that you would watch me from afar.

1571
02:32:24,481 --> 02:32:28,651
While I was tied down to the Moon Tree
and filled with grudges,

1572
02:32:29,736 --> 02:32:31,646
my words tied you down here...

1573
02:32:34,866 --> 02:32:36,656
and stopped you from leaving.

1574
02:32:47,253 --> 02:32:48,343
I...

1575
02:32:51,633 --> 02:32:53,513
have emptied everything now.

1576
02:32:58,598 --> 02:33:00,518
So you should stop now.

1577
02:33:04,437 --> 02:33:05,897
This is really...

1578
02:33:09,651 --> 02:33:11,441
the end for us.

1579
02:33:17,075 --> 02:33:18,075
Yes.

1580
02:33:21,037 --> 02:33:22,457
It's the end.

1581
02:34:51,961 --> 02:34:56,721
His soul doesn't have the energy
to go to the afterlife.

1582
02:34:57,592 --> 02:35:00,262
If we leave him here, he will vanish.

1583
02:35:01,262 --> 02:35:04,272
He won't be able to have another life.

1584
02:35:08,728 --> 02:35:10,608
To avoid that,

1585
02:35:12,315 --> 02:35:13,855
you should

1586
02:35:14,901 --> 02:35:16,191
send him off.

1587
02:35:18,196 --> 02:35:22,026
That is the last punishment

1588
02:35:22,700 --> 02:35:24,790
you will get here.

1589
02:37:18,941 --> 02:37:20,321
Yeong-su.

1590
02:37:23,780 --> 02:37:25,070
Are you up?

1591
02:37:26,032 --> 02:37:29,582
You two got really drunk,
so Mr. Koo told me to escort you home.

1592
02:37:29,660 --> 02:37:31,040
So I called a cab.

1593
02:37:31,871 --> 02:37:34,541
Well, you two can go home
on your own, right?

1594
02:37:35,249 --> 02:37:37,379
-Yes.
-Goodbye then.

1595
02:37:43,508 --> 02:37:45,428
Gosh, this again?

1596
02:37:46,677 --> 02:37:50,927
When I came to the hotel last time,
she was the one who sent me home in a cab.

1597
02:37:51,599 --> 02:37:54,979
But this time,
I remember up to drinking the cocktail.

1598
02:38:02,401 --> 02:38:03,991
Yeong-su, why are you crying?

1599
02:38:04,320 --> 02:38:07,030
I don't know. I just feel sad.

1600
02:38:09,242 --> 02:38:13,162
Seeing you cry like this is
making me sad too.

1601
02:38:16,165 --> 02:38:17,745
This is so weird.

1602
02:38:18,251 --> 02:38:20,001
I'm right here. Why are you crying?

1603
02:38:20,962 --> 02:38:21,962
Don't cry.

1604
02:38:33,141 --> 02:38:35,891
Is he really not going to make up with me?

1605
02:38:49,740 --> 02:38:51,530
We met for the first time

1606
02:38:52,285 --> 02:38:53,865
on May 2nd.

1607
02:39:20,605 --> 02:39:21,685
I found it.

1608
02:39:28,571 --> 02:39:31,701
This watch looks pretty old.

1609
02:39:31,949 --> 02:39:33,909
It's over 70 years old.

1610
02:39:34,535 --> 02:39:36,445
Time on that watch

1611
02:39:36,537 --> 02:39:39,367
has been flowing since you were alive.

1612
02:39:39,457 --> 02:39:41,127
It must be really rare.

1613
02:39:41,792 --> 02:39:43,542
It must've been hard to find it.

1614
02:39:44,837 --> 02:39:45,837
Thank you.

1615
02:39:47,048 --> 02:39:49,128
And I'm sorry.

1616
02:39:52,595 --> 02:39:56,305
I wanted to remind you
that you're 70 years older than me.

1617
02:39:56,390 --> 02:39:58,640
It wasn't easy to get that watch.

1618
02:39:58,893 --> 02:40:01,773
So from now on,

1619
02:40:02,146 --> 02:40:05,896
even if I get to look older than you
like your sister,

1620
02:40:05,983 --> 02:40:09,493
don't forget
that you are way older than I am.

1621
02:40:12,949 --> 02:40:16,039
Put it on your wrist.
I'm sure it'll look great on you.

1622
02:40:18,204 --> 02:40:19,214
Yu-na.

1623
02:40:19,997 --> 02:40:22,917
I will leave soon.

1624
02:40:24,919 --> 02:40:27,459
I told you that I was waiting
for my sister, Hyeon-mi.

1625
02:40:29,674 --> 02:40:33,094
Right now, Hyeon-mi is very sick.

1626
02:40:35,263 --> 02:40:36,643
When she leaves,

1627
02:40:37,723 --> 02:40:39,353
I must go with her.

1628
02:40:42,478 --> 02:40:43,598
Yu-na,

1629
02:40:44,480 --> 02:40:48,030
when this watch was made,

1630
02:40:49,777 --> 02:40:51,317
I had already been dead.

1631
02:40:53,155 --> 02:40:55,025
Time can't run

1632
02:40:55,825 --> 02:40:58,615
for the dead and for the living together.

1633
02:41:04,500 --> 02:41:06,710
I died too early.

1634
02:41:11,132 --> 02:41:12,632
It's so upsetting.

1635
02:41:34,572 --> 02:41:36,032
I'll see him off.

1636
02:41:38,409 --> 02:41:39,829
You'll be back soon, right?

1637
02:41:41,620 --> 02:41:42,620
Of course.

1638
02:41:43,372 --> 02:41:44,622
I'll be back soon.

1639
02:42:05,686 --> 02:42:07,016
You are coming back, right?

1640
02:42:14,945 --> 02:42:16,355
Wait for me.

1641
02:42:53,818 --> 02:42:57,278
THE SAMDO RIVER.
THIS WORLD, THE AFTERLIFE.

1642
02:43:13,421 --> 02:43:18,591
A MONTH LATER

1643
02:43:31,814 --> 02:43:34,784
Ma'am, let me help you.

1644
02:43:38,571 --> 02:43:39,821
Once you go out to the beach,

1645
02:43:39,905 --> 02:43:42,405
you can rent any kinds of beach supplies.

1646
02:43:42,491 --> 02:43:43,581
Let's go.

1647
02:43:43,659 --> 02:43:45,579
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

1648
02:43:53,419 --> 02:43:54,749
It looks like you've made progress.

1649
02:43:56,005 --> 02:43:57,465
Could you read it for me?

1650
02:44:02,928 --> 02:44:07,308
It's been a month since Ms. Jang left.

1651
02:44:07,391 --> 02:44:08,891
Ms. Jang isn't here.

1652
02:44:09,852 --> 02:44:12,062
But how come
the hotel hasn't vanished yet?

1653
02:44:12,146 --> 02:44:16,396
It means that Ms. Jang is no longer
the owner of the Guest House of the Moon.

1654
02:44:17,193 --> 02:44:19,243
That's my guess.

1655
02:44:23,699 --> 02:44:24,779
Mr. Koo.

1656
02:44:26,577 --> 02:44:29,247
I think you should go see the garden.

1657
02:44:36,754 --> 02:44:37,924
Yesterday,

1658
02:44:38,589 --> 02:44:41,259
I saw a few leaves and flowers.

1659
02:44:41,592 --> 02:44:43,432
But the tree is completely lifeless now.

1660
02:44:46,680 --> 02:44:47,930
I guess

1661
02:44:48,599 --> 02:44:51,769
that means Ms. Jang can't come back
for good now.

1662
02:45:30,724 --> 02:45:32,234
Wait for me.

1663
02:45:47,992 --> 02:45:49,202
Jang Man-wol.

1664
02:45:51,495 --> 02:45:52,655
Please hurry.

1665
02:45:54,164 --> 02:45:55,374
I'm getting...

1666
02:45:57,918 --> 02:45:59,208
anxious now.

1667
02:46:07,052 --> 02:46:10,722
All of us are against having a new owner.

1668
02:46:11,640 --> 02:46:13,520
Help Ms. Jang return.

1669
02:46:17,062 --> 02:46:18,362
I'm with them.

1670
02:46:19,440 --> 02:46:22,320
It took me 500 years
to get used to Ms. Jang.

1671
02:46:22,401 --> 02:46:24,781
Having another boss? I'm against it.

1672
02:46:27,364 --> 02:46:30,494
It is up to her
whether she returns to this place or not.

1673
02:46:30,576 --> 02:46:33,866
There's no way she won't come back
when Mr. Koo is waiting for her.

1674
02:46:35,664 --> 02:46:37,584
If she set foot on the bridge,

1675
02:46:38,375 --> 02:46:40,205
she might have forgotten him.

1676
02:48:25,858 --> 02:48:28,528
She might have let go
of all her memories of this world

1677
02:48:29,570 --> 02:48:31,780
and crossed the bridge,

1678
02:48:32,906 --> 02:48:35,276
following her most distant memories.

1679
02:48:43,876 --> 02:48:46,836
Is that why all the flowers fell?

1680
02:48:47,337 --> 02:48:50,087
Then I guess the tree is really dead now.

1681
02:48:50,674 --> 02:48:51,724
Right.

1682
02:48:53,093 --> 02:48:55,183
All the flowers fall down and disappeared.

1683
02:48:56,013 --> 02:48:57,473
I suppose Man-wol is

1684
02:48:58,265 --> 02:49:00,595
really dead now.

1685
02:49:07,399 --> 02:49:10,439
Should we be expecting a new owner
of the Guest House of the Moon?

1686
02:49:13,030 --> 02:49:17,370
The Moon Tree is the owner
of the guest house.

1687
02:49:17,576 --> 02:49:21,906
But all the flowers and leaves are gone.
It's dead now.

1688
02:49:42,935 --> 02:49:45,895
THE GUYS WHO DIED AFTER EATING

1689
02:49:53,737 --> 02:49:55,697
This is so hot.

1690
02:49:55,781 --> 02:49:58,531
How did Kim Jun-hyun
eat five of these at once?

1691
02:49:58,700 --> 02:50:00,540
He amazed me.

1692
02:50:01,578 --> 02:50:04,498
That's where Kim Jun-hyun sat.

1693
02:50:04,998 --> 02:50:06,208
Eat before it gets cold.

1694
02:50:06,291 --> 02:50:07,541
KIM JUN-HYUN SAT HERE

1695
02:50:08,669 --> 02:50:11,549
"To Ms. Jang man-wol, I love you"?

1696
02:50:11,964 --> 02:50:14,304
-Doesn't it make you happy?
-Are you confessing your love to me?

1697
02:50:14,383 --> 02:50:16,763
This is Kim Jun-hyun's autograph.
Here, "Kim Jun-hyun."

1698
02:50:17,511 --> 02:50:20,061
It's too heartbreaking
if I remain only as a flower petal

1699
02:50:21,265 --> 02:50:22,975
that's bound to vanish.

1700
02:50:27,187 --> 02:50:29,937
I'LL VISIT EVERY FAMOUS RESTAURANT
IN THIS COUNTRY

1701
02:51:26,413 --> 02:51:30,793
Not all of the flowers vanished.

1702
02:51:35,422 --> 02:51:37,972
There are still some flowers left.

1703
02:51:46,308 --> 02:51:48,808
I put the flowers dreaming of the moon

1704
02:51:49,478 --> 02:51:51,728
in his heart.

1705
02:53:22,738 --> 02:53:24,908
Subtitle translation by Wayne Ryu
